Dear Den, Thank you for taking the time to share your feedback, and please accept our sincerest apologies for your recent experiences at our resort. We are extremely concerned to hear about the incident involving your meal and are very sorry for the distress this caused you. This is absolutely not the level of safety, quality, or care that we strive to provide to our guests. Please be assured that this matter has been taken very seriously. Our Food & Beverage and Culinary teams have conducted a full investigation and implemented additional quality control checks to ensure this does not happen again. We appreciate that our manager was able to speak with you at the time, and we regret that your stay was impacted so negatively. We also apologise for the separate experience at breakfast and the delay in service. Your comments have been shared directly with our restaurant management team, and retraining is already underway to improve both food preparation and service consistency. Your feedback is invaluable in helping us improve, and we deeply regret that your stay did not reflect the high standards we aim to uphold. We sincerely hope you might reconsider in the future and allow us the opportunity to restore your confidence in Accor and our Darwin Airport properties. Warm regards, The Team at Novotel, Mercure & Ibis Darwin Airport Customer review rating 1.0/5 Helen C. Families - 11/11/2025 Confirmed reviews ALL Booked a staycation with family to celebrate a birthday and wish we‚Äôd have stayed elsewhere. Pool was great but there was so service available around the pool or even through the cabana that we booked despite QR codes on every single table saying we could order and collect. Room was OK, bathroom smelt of sewerage throughout the entire stay but aircon was cold, probably the one good thing about the room. We decided to try the pool side restaurant for dinner and after picking a table we were asked to move as it was ‚Äúbooked‚Äù, moved to a table under the window and froze under the aircon before realising the table next to where we originally wanted to sit was now free so we asked to move. Staff did not clean the table and we had to ask for new glasses and cutlery. Drinks took 30mins to arrive and appetisers arrived first. We ordered the ceviche and it was rotten, the fish itself smelt so bad and was gray. We alerted staff immediately and were lectured on 2 separate occasions by 2 different staff members about ceviche being raw fish‚Ä¶ (we often enjoy ceviche regularly as we fish a lot and prepare it ourselves) very patronising and we decided to cancel the rest of the food and catch a cab into town. Upon returning to the hotel at 10.30pm the staff were unwelcoming and as a female, I felt intimated by the night staff around the hotel. Safe to say we won‚Äôt be back to stay‚Ä¶ See more See more about the review from Helen C. Our hotel has responded to the review Our hotel has responded to the review from Helen C. Dear Helen, Thank you for taking the time to share such detailed feedback about your recent stay. We are very sorry to hear that your experience did not meet expectations, particularly on what should have been a special and relaxing family celebration. Please accept our sincerest apologies for the issues you encountered ‚Äî from the service delays and maintenance concerns in your room, to the disappointing experience in the restaurant. The quality of food you described and the way your concern was handled are unacceptable and well below our standards. We have shared your comments directly with our Food & Beverage and Culinary teams for urgent review and retraining. We are also sorry that you felt uncomfortable upon returning later in the evening. The safety and comfort of our guests are our highest priorities, and we will be following up with our night team to ensure our service remains professional and welcoming at all times. We truly appreciate you highlighting both the positives, such as our pool and air conditioning, and the areas where we must do better. Your feedback helps us make meaningful improvements to the overall guest experience. Thank you again for bringing this to our attention, and please know that your comments are being taken seriously. We hope you might consider giving us another opportunity in the future to provide the quality stay and service you rightfully expected. name: Ballina Fishermen's Co-Op
homepage_content: Ballina Fishermens Co-Op | Your Local for Cooked and Fresh Seafood PHONE ORDERS: (02) 6686 2533 Facebook Instagram Facebook Instagram Your local for‚Ä¶.Cooked and Fresh Seafood PHONE ORDERS: (02) 6686 2533 OPENING HOURS Monday: 10am ‚Äì 6pm Tuesday: 10am ‚Äì 6pm Wednesday: 10am ‚Äì 6pm Thursday: 10am ‚Äì 6pm Friday: 10am ‚Äì 7pm Saturday: 10am ‚Äì 7pm Sunday: 10am ‚Äì 6pm The town of Ballina has the BIG Prawn, and that is for a good reason! Our local King prawn is famous for its delicious taste with firm crisp sweet flavour. The Ballina Fishermen‚Äôs Co-op is owned by the towns local fishermen who bring their catch in to be sold in their shop. The variety on offer can vary as different species of seafood come and go in different seasons. We try to rely on our Local Fishermen as much as possible so we can supply you with the best local seafood in Ballina, However bad weather is inevitable, so when we have bad weather we still try to supply you with the best seafood from within Australia. A normal day in the shop would see a selection of fresh Whole fish and fillets ranging from Snapper, Mackerel, Whiting, Mullet, Salmon, Barramundi and any other Delights our Fishermen bring us, You will also find fresh oysters, Local Peeled Green King Prawns, Mud Crabs, Spanner Crabs, Sand Crabs, Cooked Local King Prawns and Balmain Bugs. We also offer cooked seafood using only Australian fish & New Zealand Hoki. We make our own Prawn Cutlets & Whiting, We have all your takeaway favorites with a choice of 6 different Burgers and a huge hot food range from Potato Scallops to Pineapple Fritters!

name: Collins Court Butcher
homepage_content: Home | Collins Court Butchers | Mount Gambier | SA ABOUT US Mick Lamond has been working in the meat industry for almost two decades and in July 2006 branched out on his own and set up Collins Court Butchers. Back then, it was a two person operation but from little things, big things grew, and after setting up a loyal customer base and securing wholesale contracts to the region‚Äôs pubs and sporting clubs, all within two years, Collins Court Butchers started to expand. Today Mick employs six staff and the business shows no signs of slowing. Priding themselves on sourcing locally produced beef, lamb and pork, Collins Court Butchers has the runs on the board in terms of industry accolades as well. In 2017 they took out the Australian Meat Industry Council‚Äôs Sausage King Competition for best pork sausage in South Australia, finishing second nationwide, with their beef & chicken sausages finishing second in the South Australian event. Customer service and using locally sourced product are the other cornerstones to the Collins Court Butcher business. ‚ÄúCustomer service is the most important thing,‚Äù Mick said. ‚ÄúWe are always trying to help our customers and we will source anything for them or do anything for them that we can. homepage_content: emjayscoffee Skip to content Item added to your cart View my cart Check out Continue shopping Select Specialty Coffee Beans Roasted fresh to order & delivered straight to your door. BUY COFFEE ONLINE ABOUT US THE EMJAYS EXPERIENCE emjays is a coffee shop and coffee roaster serving amazing quality coffee. We pride ourselves on the quality of our coffee, selecting only the very best organic coffee beans. Each coffee poured at emjays is created using the emjays house blend which is an exquisite blend of the very best organic coffee beans available. We have been proudly roasting and delivering coffee Australia wide now since 2008. We take the upmost of care in the quality of our product. In our cafes you can expect a nice relaxed atmosphere with exceptional coffee. Life is too precious to waste on a bad cup of coffee. READ MORE OUR COFFEE Passion for Coffee When it comes to our beans we pride ourselves on the quality of our coffee, selecting only the very best organic coffee beans to give you the ultimate coffee experience. Free Wifi Here at Emjays we offer free WiFi at all our locations! Please ask our friendly staff for the password to get connected. name: Fremantle BeerFest
homepage_content: Fremantle BeerFest 2025 Home Page Freo BeerFest is back 14-16 November! 14 -16 NOVEMBER | ESPLANADE PARK, FREMANTLE 500+ BEERS ‚Ä¢ CIDER ‚Ä¢ THE PRESETS DJ SET ‚Ä¢ END OF FASHION ‚Ä¢ DEATH BY DENIM ‚Ä¢ NEWPORT ‚Ä¢ GOURMET FOOD ‚Ä¢ COMEDY ‚Ä¢ PRO WRESTLING ‚Ä¢ MASTERCLASSES ‚Ä¢ COCKTAIL MAKING ‚Ä¢ TATTOOS ‚Ä¢ BEER OLYMPICS ‚Ä¢ BEER YOGA ‚Ä¢ AXE THROWING ‚Ä¢ WAVE SIMULATOR ‚Ä¢ FIRE TWIRLERS ‚Ä¢ BEER PONG + SO MUCH MORE GET TICKETS ACCOMMODATION Welcome to Fremantle BeerFest Since 2011, BeerFest has brought together the best in craft beer, cider, and cocktails, perfectly paired with indulgent street food, for a festival overflowing with flavour and fun. But there‚Äôs nowhere quite like Fremantle to host this party. As the original home of Australian craft beer, Freo sets the perfect stage for the largest celebration of the very best WA producers , all in one place . From stouts to sours, crisp ciders to experimental ales, you‚Äôll sip your way through over 300 unique, small-batch and limited-edition brews, plus wild cocktail creations and exclusive collaborations. All this, served up alongside mouthwatering street-eats and good vibes by the pint. A full-pour celebration of great drinks & good times across four massive sessions: Friday 14 Nov | Night Session 5PM ‚Äì 10PM Saturday 15 Nov | Day Session 11AM ‚Äì 4PM Saturday 15 Nov | Night Session 5PM ‚Äì 10PM Sunday 16 Nov | Day Session 12PM ‚Äì 5PM Come to one ‚Äì or come to all! This year, we raise a very special toast to 25 years of Little Creatures , the hometown legends who helped shape the craft scene we know and love. Expect big brews, birthday surprises, and a whole lot of hometown pride. With live music featuring The Presets (DJ Set) End Of Fashion, Death By Denim + Newport , stand-up comedy featuring Tom Ballard , Luke Joseph Ryan , Andrew Wolfe , Gillian Cordiner and Chris Pucillo; roving performers, food and drink masterclasses, DIY workshops and the legendary Beer Olympics, Freo BeerFest 2025 is shaping up to be our biggest and boldest celebration yet. Bring your crew, your appetite and your curiosity- there‚Äôs something here for everyone. Let the good times pour! Previous Previous Previous Next Next Next THE DRINKS Tap into over 500 premium pours from WA‚Äôs biggest names in beer, cider, spirits, seltzers and wine. Think bold brews, zesty sours, crisp ciders, cheeky slushies, session-ready seltzers, and cocktail creations that‚Äôll blow your tastebuds away. THE FOOD Sink your teeth into a sizzling spread of gourmet street eats of all varieties ‚Äî where local legends dish up juicy, spicy, crispy, sweet, and downright irresistible flavours from every corner of the globe. MASTER CLASSES Explore a world of flavour through our hands-on Masterclasses, where tasting meets learning in the most delicious way. From beer and doughnuts to wine and cheese, and cocktails paired with chocolate, you‚Äôll discover surprising combinations and the stories behind them. Led by local brewers, distillers, and food artisans, each session offers expert insights, fun facts, and plenty of chances to meet the legends behind your favourite sips and bites. LIVE COMEDY Festivalgoers can laugh out loud with a lager in hand at the Fresh Comedy live comedy stage, hosting a slew of local and national iconic funny men and women including Australia‚Äôs most legendary comedians. ACCOMMODATION PACKAGES WITH ESPLANADE HOTEL FREMANTLE BY RYDGES The iconic The Esplanade Hotel Fremantle by Rydges is the perfect choice for accommodation when staying in Fremantle for BeerFest. Located directly opposite the park you are in the heart of the action from the moment you arrive and only a short walk across the road when you are ready to have a rest from all the fun at BeerFest. The hotel is a 4.5 star property with four bars and restaurants, 2 swimming pools, 24 reception and room service and self parking. The perfect place to unwind after a busy day. For more details and to order these packages, please check our ticketing page . MAKE YOUR MARK IN THE MOST MEMORABLE WAY POSSIBLE Our mates at Ink Carts Tattoos are teaming up with Campus Brewing to bring you some fun flash and maybe something a little special! Ink Carts will have sheets of flash available for festivalgoers to choose from. Their talented and experienced artists have selectively drawn 50+ fun and creative designs including some BeerFest specific designs that everyone can get into ‚Äì all only $100! UNLEASH THE POWER OF PRO WRESTLING WITH EPW PERTH! Get ready to experience the thrill and adrenaline of live wrestling like never before! Western Australia‚Äôs premiere Pro Wrestling organisation ‚Äì EPW Perth is bringing the heat to our event with larger-than-life personalities, and action-packed entertainment. With wild action, jaw dropping manoeuvres and bodies flying off the top rope, you can be sure to be amazed by the finest Pro Wrestler‚Äôs in Australia. WITH THANKS TO OUR PARTNERS Stay in touch with our socials. facebook instagram Scroll to top Scroll to top Scroll to top

name: Henri's Wodonga Bakery
homepage_content: Bakery in Wodonga | Henri‚Äôs Wodonga Bakery 02 6024 1248 We Are Now Open! Weekdays from 6am - 4:30pm and Weekends from 7am - 2pm HOME OF THE WORLD'S LARGEST ROLLING PIN! Henri's Wodonga Bakery Where something good is always cooking. Something for everyone, healthy or naughty! Call Today Award Winning Bakery Here at Henri‚Äôs Wodonga Bakery, there‚Äôs something for everyone! Follow the irresistible aromas and step inside for a delicious bite to eat, sit-down meal or a takeaway treat. At our friendly bakery you‚Äôll find an awesome array of freshly baked goods, both sweet and savoury to choose from. Pick up a pie or pasty or indulge your sweet tooth with scones, sponges, and many more delicious dessert options. Sit in and enjoy our cafe‚Äôs breakfast and lunch menus . Ôªø At Henri‚Äôs Wodonga Bakery, we buy all our supplies from local butcher and grocers, and we‚Äôre proud to support our local community. Our family-owned business, friendly atmosphere, and great service has made us a firm favourite in Wodonga, and we‚Äôre proud of the relationships we‚Äôve built with both locals and visitors. While you‚Äôre here, don‚Äôt miss out on grabbing a photo with the world‚Äôs largest rolling pin sitting atop our bakery! Weighing in at 2-tonnes and 14-metres long, Henri‚Äôs Wodonga Bakery is pretty hard to miss! For custom orders, or any other enquiries, just give us a call and we‚Äôll be happy to help. Call Today Menu Catering Menu Planning an event? Our catering menu includes a mouth-watering selection of both sweet and savoury options. From finger food to full meals, there‚Äôs something for every occasion. If it‚Äôs not on the menu, give us a call to discuss your needs. Learn More Shop Menu Kick start your day with a big breakfast or treat yourself to a tasty lunch from Henri‚Äôs Wodonga Bakery. Find delicious coffees and milkshakes, there‚Äôs something to satisfy every craving! Learn More Fresh & Frozen Take Home Foods Grab a delicious meal from the freezer or the counter and enjoy it at home with our range of fresh and frozen take home foods. We have plenty of gluten-free options in the freezer, plus a range of homemade soups, pastas, and much more. Learn More Testimonials I arrived early as I needed my car serviced and we were after something for breakfast. I got a sausage roll that was topped with bacon and cheese, absolutely delicious and a latte. Brought a Vienna loaf to take home. First time customers and we found it very nice. Rebecca Button Great pies, nice pastry and filling. The two for $20 family pies are great with smashed peas, yum! Tim Button Amazing food especially the orange and poppyseed muffins and custard tarts. Consistency is amazing. Definitely best bakery in town! Best bit is amazing selection (for a bakery) of gluten-free products Great for children Best biscuits Freshly baked bread Delicious pastries Homemade pies Good for breakfast Unique desserts Custom cakes Tasty cupcakes Chris Button Coming from Adelaide, I had no idea that an awesome place existed here. Best blueberry muffin I have ever tried. Johnny Button Tonight, we ordered takeaway from Henri‚Äôs Wodonga Bakery for dinner. It was the best burger we have had in ages! Everything was delicious! Support your locals, keep them going during this current crisis! Kimmy Button I‚Äôve been going here since I was little, 10+ years and it‚Äôs always been a joy. Today though, was beyond amazing. Whilst we were eating, and I was breastfeeding when a very nice lady who worked here (I didn‚Äôt grab her name) decided to bring me out a large cup of iced water because she remembered how thirsty she got whilst breastfeeding. That small bit of support and acceptance goes such a long way, I can‚Äôt thank you enough. Adele Button Love this place Staff are always friendly and a huge range of food and drinks on offer! Carris Button I had an orange and poppyseed muffin that was to die for. Staff were all so friendly and helpful and they have The Big Rolling Pin on their roof for you Australian Big Thing collectors. My pie wasn‚Äôt to my taste, it was more of a mince style filling than the cubed meat but still had plenty of flavour. Deanna Button These guys make the best slices in town. So reasonably priced and delish. Hard to not buy a treat or 2 while in there. Service is always outstanding. Great work guys xx Domonique Button Why has nobody mentioned the rolling pin? It's the biggest one in the world. They say you can actually see it from space. Henri's also does great pies. As a self-proclaimed pie aficionado, I am yet to have a better pie on the border. Andy Button Very nice and helpful staff, they made me feel like family. Wickedest Z. Button Henri's Wodonga Bakery is fabulous. It has a fresh juice bar, sells all sorts of meat pies and sausage rolls, plus sandwiches of all kinds. Their pastries are great, and they sell a pink icing vanilla slice. I was recently driving through at lunch time and bought a potato pie with tomato sauce. It had a wonderful flavour. Not too salty, not too hot, the meat and gravy mixed nicely with the potato mash on the top which was sprinkled with bacon bits. Gary Button Wonderful place. The food is always fantastic and the staff awesome. Always love going there after work for a quick coffee and cake while having down time. Highly recommended. Zoe Button Had a great curry pie and an awesome freshly squeezed juice. Mark Button Food is always amazing, and they have friendly staff. Always busy in the place but staff try their hardest to get through as many people as fast as they can. Best pumpkin bread you'll ever eat, if you've never tried it you absolutely have to!! Love their juice and smoothie range and the coffees are always nice and the donuts are amazing!! Best bakery on the border!! Myranda Button Best iced donuts and lovely, friendly service! Rhonda Button Really good variety of all the things you would expect at a traditional bakery. Cake selection is really good, and their bread roll selection is very good. Pies and sausage rolls etc pretty good. Often gets busy and service is efficient and good. I would give it a 5 if the dining inside was modernised and felt a little nicer to eat in. homepage_content: Pax Hill Pizza | Official Website VISIT US 25 Barker Cres, Traralgon CALL US (03) 5174 2980 Our History Welcome to Pax Hill Pizza, where passion meets perfection in every slice! Established in 1989, Pax Hill Pizza has been serving the community with mouthwatering pizzas for over three decades. With our commitment to quality ingredients and authentic flavors, we have become a beloved pizza destination in the heart of Traralgon Our Menu At Pax Hill Pizza, we take pride in crafting pizzas that are a delight to both the eyes and taste buds. Our menu boasts a wide range of traditional and innovative toppings, from classic Margherita to gourmet combinations like Chicken Tandoori and Seafood. Each pizza is carefully handcrafted by our skilled pizza makers, ensuring that every bite is a burst of deliciousness. And for those seeking something beyond pizza, we also offer a selection of delectable pastas, sides, and desserts to complete your dining experience. We also cater for vegetarian and gluten-free dietary requirements, so no one has to miss out! Our Services In addition to our exceptional food, Pax Hill Pizza offers a range of services to cater to your needs. Whether you prefer the convenience of pickup or the comfort of home delivery, we've got you covered. Our friendly staff is dedicated to providing prompt and reliable service, ensuring that your pizza arrives hot and fresh at your doorstep. We offer delivery services to Traralgon and a large range of suburbs. Catering For larger gatherings or special events, we also offer catering services, creating a memorable culinary experience for you and your guests. To place an order for catering, simply give us a call on: (03) 5174 2980 , or send us an email: gary@paxhillpizza.com . Contact us today! REVIEWS Best pizza in Traralgon. Nothing comes close. Really happy with their generosity with the fillings. Amazing customer service too. Would give 10 stars. - Thomas T. Pizzas were great, steaming hot on delivery & all were very delicious. Fresh dough, premium ingredients, cooked to perfection, what more could a girl ask for? A huge thank you for always getting my pizza right. - Kim F. Great service from a great team. The best in town. Value for money. - Cass Still the best Hawaiian I√¢¬Ä¬ôve ever tasted, and my favourite garlic bread. Quick delivery and great food, won√¢¬Ä¬ôt go anywhere else. - Jodie C. Easy online ordering and payment. Ready at the time specified and was prepared as ordered. Good pizza with plenty of topping. - Leanne S. We ordered the Italian pizza without anchovies and it was cooked very quickly. The pizza toppings were delicious and well balanced, and the base was lovely and crispy. Perfect!. - Cindy C. name: Whyalla Wetlands
homepage_content: Whyalla South Australia for extraordinary Natural Wonders EXPLORE CUTTLEFEST Snorkel or dive with our Australian Giant Cuttlefish EXPLORE CUTTLEFEST Witness a globally unique phenomenon EXPLORE CUTTLEFEST Drive along the cuttlefish coastline EXPLORE CUTTLEFEST See the incredible cuttlefish themed art around Whyalla Whyalla, south australia Unearth unforgettable experiences; Whyalla offers natural wonders contrasted with industry in vivid landscapes, aquatic serenity, sea life and great adventures. Located on Eyre Peninsula‚Äôs Spencer Gulf in South Australia, Whyalla is an important hub and the region‚Äôs biggest city for retail shopping. Whyalla boasts a warm climate, accessible ocean shores and saltwater fishing. Whyalla represents South Australia‚Äôs foremost combination of industrial and nature-based experiences. With vivid scenery, small city charm, distinctive mystic outback landscapes and year-round things to do, Whyalla offers discovery, unique Australian natural wonders and absolute contrast in nature based and industrial activities. Activities that are significant to the landscape and geography of the region that will enthral and gratify those looking to unearth and experience learning, adventure time and witness unrivalled sights and happenings. Cuttlefest Be brave this winter, and unearth adventure. Discover a vibrant underwater world and witness a globally unique phenomenon. Living in Whyalla Whyalla is more than just a place to visit ‚Äì it‚Äôs a city of opportunity that you‚Äôll fall in love with and never want to leave. The Whyalla Jetty Take a self guided tour of the new Whyalla Jetty today Whyalla Visitor Centre Whyalla‚Äôs central location makes it easily accessible and ideally located for touring, holidaying and living a great lifestyle. Find out about travel and transport, weather, maps and more. Experience Whyalla Whyalla is famous for our captivating cuttlefish and dolphins, steelworks industry and nature based activities. Unearth natural wonders, experiences and landscapes. Book a tour Step aboard a WWII vessel built right here in Whyalla, Learn of steelmaking, ship building and the heritage of our beautiful region. You will be awed by the dramatic events and vivid colours and textures that shape Whyalla. Witness the spectacle the Whyalla steelworks and learn about the transformation of ore into steel; wonder at the antics of the local resident dolphins and feel the sand between your toes when searching for a delicious meal of fresh crab off the Whyalla Foreshore beach. Witness the camouflage and colourful mating rituals of Whyalla‚Äôs distinctive giant cuttlefish; Relax within the ocean and wonders of the unique Northern Coastline and beaches on the tranquil Spencer Gulf, set against backdrop of the ancient Southern Flinders Ranges. Check out the video below and discover some of the many reasons why you should Unearth Your Next Step in Whyalla! homepage_content: Aboriginal Bush Traders: Aboriginal Art gallery, retail store and cafe Skip to content Close menu Home Shop Caf√© What's On Corporate Gifts Catering About Us Our History Artists & Suppliers Contact/FAQ's Log in Facebook Instagram WELCOME TO ABORIGINAL BUSH TRADERS A 100% not-for-profit organisation committed to selling ethically sourced and sustainable products that directly support local Indigenous communities. The story behind the Green Ant Logo. The three green ants: Aboriginal People and Aboriginal Bush Traders with Industry/Government working together towards creating a secure and sustainable economic future (the nest) for Aboriginal people. The logo also feature raark (cross hatching) which is typically found in Top End artworks, signifying our regional interest. You can't build a strong nest without working together. exhibition Ngaruwanajirri Bark Painting NOW! At Wurrumiyanga on Bathurst Island, one beautiful building known as the Tiwi Sistine Chapel or The Keeping Place houses a small group of Tiwi artists who attend daily to create artwork in a peaceful environment. The artists are guided towards excellence in their finished artworks and are represented in State Galleries across Australia and over the world. Renowned for their use of traditional Tiwi cultural materials such as ground-up local ochre pigments, artists also work with a variety of contemporary media including wax and dyes on silk. Aboriginal Art Christmas Decorations View all Quick view Tina Martin Xmas Ball $14.00 Quick view Jacinta Numina Assorted Hand Painted Bush Medicine Leaves Christmas Decorations $12.00 Quick view Betsy Lewis Mina Mina Dreaming Xmas Ball $14.00 Quick view Julie Woods Two Sisters Xmas Ball $14.00 View all 12 products Tina Martin Xmas Ball Regular price $14.00 8 in stock Size: 7.6cm "Close (esc)" Jacinta Numina Assorted Hand Painted Bush Medicine Leaves Christmas Decorations Regular price $12.00 81 in stock These Hand Painted Christmas Decorations come in different shapes and designs. Online orders will be a random selection "Close (esc)" Betsy Lewis Mina Mina Dreaming Xmas Ball Regular price $14.00 37 in stock Xmas Ball - 7.6cm-BLE611 The country associated with this painting is Mina Mina, a place far west of Yuendumu, significant to Napangardi and Napanangka women who are the custodians of the Jukurrpa that created the area. The Dreaming describes the journey of a group of women of all ages who travelled east gathering food, collecting Ngalyipi (Tinospora smilacina or snake vine) and performing ceremonies as they travelled. The women began their journey at Mina Mina where Karlangu (digging sticks) emerged from the ground. Taking these implements the women travelled east creating Janyinki and other sites. Their journey took them eventually beyond Warlpiri country. In contemporary Warlpiri paintings traditional iconography is used to represent the Jukurrpa, associated sites and other elements. The primary motif used in paintings of the Jukurrpa are the Karlangu digging sticks which rose up out of the ground at Mina Mina. The women used them to collect bush tucker on their travels. This painting shows the motion of the digging sticks as the women move them to dig. September 12, 2023 Tourism Chillout Travel Winery Tours Embarking on a wine tour of the Yarra Valley promises a delightful journey through lush vineyards, picturesque landscapes, and an abundance of delectable wines. Whether you‚Äôre a wine connoisseur or a casual enthusiast, the Yarra Valley offers an unforgettable experience that blends the elegance of wine tasting with the beauty of nature. While planning your visit, it‚Äôs crucial to consider the perfect outfit that seamlessly combines comfort, style, and practicality for a day filled with wine, food, and scenic beauty. The Yarra Valley Wine Tour Experience Before diving into the details of what to wear on your Yarra Valley wine tour, let‚Äôs take a moment to appreciate what makes this experience so special. Nestled in the heart of Victoria, Australia, the Yarra Valley boasts a unique terroir that produces exceptional cool-climate wines. Rolling hills covered in vineyards stretch as far as the eye can see, creating a mesmerizing backdrop for your wine adventure. During your wine tour of the Yarra Valley, you‚Äôll have the opportunity to visit world-renowned wineries, taste a variety of exquisite wines, savor gourmet cuisine, and enjoy the region‚Äôs serene beauty. The tour typically involves a combination of wine tastings, vineyard tours, and indulgent meals, making it essential to choose an outfit that can effortlessly transition between these activities. The Perfect Yarra Valley Wine Tour Outfit Now, let‚Äôs delve into the details of what you should wear to make the most of your Yarra Valley wine tour. Comfortable Footwear Walking through vineyards and winery tours are integral parts of the Yarra Valley wine tour experience. To ensure comfort throughout the day, opt for comfortable and supportive footwear. Closed-toe shoes, such as stylish sneakers or comfortable loafers, are ideal for navigating uneven terrain and ensuring you‚Äôre ready for any spontaneous vineyard exploration. Weather-Appropriate Attire The Yarra Valley‚Äôs weather can be quite variable, so it‚Äôs essential to check the forecast before your visit. During the warm months, lightweight, breathable clothing like sundresses, shorts, and short-sleeve shirts are perfect. In cooler weather, layering is your best friend. Consider wearing a light sweater or cardigan over a blouse or shirt, along with comfortable jeans or trousers. Sun Protection The Yarra Valley‚Äôs sunny climate can be both a blessing and a potential source of discomfort. Be sure to pack sunglasses, a wide-brimmed hat or cap, and sunscreen with a high SPF rating to protect your skin from the sun‚Äôs rays during outdoor tastings and vineyard tours. Wine Tour Accessories To enhance your wine tour experience, bring along a few essential accessories. A lightweight scarf can add a touch of style and keep you warm if the weather changes unexpectedly. A crossbody bag or a small backpack is perfect for carrying essentials like your wallet, phone, and a water bottle. Layers for Winery Interiors Many Yarra Valley wineries have cozy and temperature-controlled interiors where you can enjoy tastings. It‚Äôs a good idea to have a layering option, like a stylish blazer or a shawl, to stay comfortable indoors without feeling too warm. Dress to Impress While comfort is key, it‚Äôs also essential to maintain a sense of style on your Yarra Valley wine tour. Dressing well shows respect for the wineries and their craft. A smart-casual outfit, such as a flowy sundress for women or slacks and a button-down shirt for men, strikes the perfect balance between comfort and sophistication. Light Outerwear Even during the warmer months, evenings in the Yarra Valley can get chilly. Consider bringing a light jacket or a stylish cardigan that compliments your outfit to stay warm during evening events or outdoor dinners. Essential Wine Tour Accessories Don‚Äôt forget to accessorize your outfit with a few wine-themed items. A wine tour of the Yarra Valley wouldn‚Äôt be complete without a wine glass necklace holder, allowing you to keep your hands free while sipping and exploring. Additionally, a wine journal or tasting notebook can help you remember your favorite wines and the wineries you visited. Conclusion As you embark on your wine tour of the Yarra Valley, remember that your choice of attire can greatly enhance your overall experience. Comfort, style, and practicality should be at the forefront of your outfit decisions. With the picturesque vineyards, world-class wineries, and delectable wines awaiting you, your well-chosen attire will ensure that your Yarra Valley wine tour is nothing short of extraordinary. So, pack your bags, put on your best wine-tour-appropriate outfit, and get ready to savor the flavors of the Yarra Valley while enjoying the perfect blend of nature, culture, and wine. ‚Ä¶ How to Manage Your Airbnb Property Portfolio Remotely September 25, 2022 Tourism Managing your Airbnb property portfolio remotely is a great way to free up time and save money. You can still be hands-on with your Airbnb property and make sure everything is running smoothly from anywhere in the world. Here are some tips on how to manage your Airbnb property portfolio remotely: Use a Calendar for Booking and Cleaning You don‚Äôt have to check in with guests every day (in fact, it might be best not to). But you do need to make sure that they have everything they need during their stay and that nothing goes wrong. Use a calendar app like Google Calendar or iCal so you can see who checked in and when and when they will be checking out. This way, if anything needs fixing, you can get in touch with the guest before they leave so they aren‚Äôt inconvenienced by having to call you at home or during work hours after arriving at their destination. Use a Virtual Assistant The best way to make sure that your property is being maintained and managed properly is by hiring a virtual assistant (VA). VAs can help with the day-to-day tasks that you don‚Äôt want to deal with yourself, like dealing with guests, cleaning up after them, and even interacting with other VAs who work on behalf of other hosts. Some VAs specializes in being ‚ÄúAirbnb concierges‚Äù ‚Äî they‚Äôll handle all aspects of guest communication and make sure everything goes smoothly during their stay. Be Sure to Set Up Email Alerts for Any Important Events As an owner, you‚Äôll want to be notified when something significant happens on your property(ies). Examples include: A guest has booked a reservation. You can set up an alert that will notify you when a new booking is made. This is especially useful if your calendar is shared with other people who need access to it (e.g., a property manager). Make Sure You Have Adequate Coverage for Your Insurance Policies Before Taking on Additional Properties In order to avoid costly mistakes, be sure that you have adequate coverage before taking on too many properties or additional responsibilities with your current properties. Use the Airbnb App as Much as Possible This includes everything from checking reservation statuses via mobile app (which lets you see how many nights each booking lasts) to communicating with guests via chat or phone calls (so long as they have provided their contact details). The more you use the app, the less time you‚Äôll have to spend futzing with spreadsheets and other apps. Use Automated Payments Automate your rent collection with a platform like RentMoola or SquareSpace. This will make it easier to keep track of all your expenses in one place, and you won‚Äôt have to worry about forgetting to send the rent check each month. Keep Track of All Your Expenses in One Place Use accounting software such as Quickbooks or Freshbooks to manage finances and create invoices for tenants. You can also use these platforms to send out reminders if they haven‚Äôt paid their rent on time. Plan ahead for Vacancies If you don‚Äôt want any vacancies in your property portfolio, then plan ahead and make sure that there are always enough people interested in renting from you at any given time. You can do this by listing multiple units at once on Airbnb, increasing your chances of filling them all up again before they go vacant. This way, you don‚Äôt have long periods of time when no money is coming in from those properties! Use Holiday House Management Services If you‚Äôre traveling during peak vacation times like Christmas or New Year‚Äôs Eve, consider hiring a professional holiday house manager to oversee your property during that time period. This person will take care of all maintenance issues before guests arrive and handle any problems that arise while they‚Äôre there ‚Äî all while ensuring that the home looks great when they leave so they can get their deposit back quickly after their stay ends. There are many holiday house management services online but it is a must to get the accredited one. Managing an Airbnb portfolio remotely can seem like quite a daunting task. However, it can be done, and in the best way possible. By carefully organizing your properties and learning how to maximize automation, you can rest assured that your strategies will be optimized and your vacation rental business will run as smoothly as possible. ‚Ä¶ How to Save Money on Business Admin Tasks August 24, 2022 Uncategorized Outsourcing business processes doesn‚Äôt mean sending jobs away overseas. It means using high-value information technologies to efficiently handle repetitive or complex tasks, freeing resources for other strategic projects. What‚Äôs the difference? For example, sometimes it is more practical to send a workforce job overseas as opposed to outsourcing. Think of your business as a department store. If you had people that worked in the basement putting boxes together and then handing them off to another group on another floor and they hand it off again to someone on another floor and so on until the very top where they put it into shipping containers and send those off to be shipped out ‚Äî that‚Äôs outsourcing but you have created your own physical infrastructure in-house that is working out of a central location (your downtown) as opposed to having everyone go out into different locations around town (outsourcers). Ways To Save Money on Business Admin Tasks Outsourcing business processes is the ability of a business to transfer key activities to dedicated specialists, who can perform those processes more effectively than the company could manage itself. This is done in the hope that this will allow the company to increase its performance and gain a competitive advantage. There are many benefits to outsourcing business processes. Improvements in Productivity By outsourcing a company‚Äôs call center, you can free up your employees to do more productive work. With an outsourced call center, staff members don‚Äôt have to answer the same questions over and over again when they already have answers readily available. Employees will be able to focus on other pressing issues that require their attention. Increased Customer Satisfaction One of the biggest advantages of outsourcing is that it enables companies to increase customer satisfaction levels by providing higher quality service than they could provide internally. Customers can contact a live person who speaks their language and understands their needs, which makes for happier customers and greater brand loyalty for your organization‚Äôs products or services Shorter Implementation Timeframes Outsourcing allows companies to quickly scale up from start-up mode into high-growth mode without having to recruit new employees or invest in training programs for internal staff members who need specialized skillsets that aren‚Äôt easily found in today‚Äôs marketplace. Cost Effective Outsourcing business processes is a cost-effective way to manage your business. By outsourcing, your company can focus on its core competencies and let a third party handle the rest. With the right service provider, you‚Äôll get more for less ‚Äî meaning that you‚Äôll spend less time and money on things like payroll, accounting, and benefits administration. Increased Flexibility Companies that outsource their business processes have more flexibility than those that don‚Äôt. For example, if your firm needs to hire an extra employee or two in order to meet a deadline or complete an important project, you can easily do so without having to consider how much it will cost or how long it will take to train them up on what they need to know in order to get started on the job right away. Better Customer Service Companies that outsource their business processes are able to provide better customer service than those that do not. This is because outsourced companies have teams of experts at their disposal who can be assigned specific tasks and compensated for doing so according to their individual skill sets and experience levels in this particular field of work (such as finance or human resources). Take Aways Outsourcing allows you to focus on the core of your business, by providing a competent team that handles your business processes for you. This not only allows for faster solutions but cheaper solutions as well. Moreover, a reliable outsourcing services provider is a trend that is here to stay. As businesses across the world continually look for ways to streamline their operations, more and more companies are either turning to offshore outsourcing or implementing automation with varying degrees of success‚Ä¶. How to prepare & recover ‚Äì Giro style November 11, 2020 Tourism The Giro d‚ÄôItalia is easily one of the world‚Äôs most stunning, albeit challenging, cycles. From the towering Alps to the formidable Dolomites and the Apennines‚Äô pristine beauty, the Giro is a passionate cyclist‚Äôs rite of passage. Any experienced cyclist will therefore know that this is not a ride to be taken lightly ‚Äì you have to prepare yourself for its gruelling ascents, some of which last for over 20kms. Not only that, when taking part in the tour you have to ensure that your body recovers in time for the next stage. Fancy riding the exact track that‚Äôs ridden during the Giro? Our partners at A‚Äôqto run cycling holidays of the Giro d‚ÄôItalia that are sure to get your blood pumping. Here are some tips for preparing and recovering like a Giro pro. Take care of your gut health Poor gut health and digestive problems often cause cyclists great trouble when traversing long passages. To prepare your gut and digestive system for your tour it is best to get started pre-tour. Cut out any foods that can irritate your stomach including acidic foods. Furthermore, reduce your intake of caffeine and alcohol whilst increasing your vegetable intake. Train regularly This cannot be stressed enough. You want to be match fit when you arrive at the Giro as it truly is a competitor‚Äôs circuit. Ensure that whenever you have the opportunity to cycle at home ‚Äì you do it. Take your training to the nearest location that is roughly similar to the Giro‚Äôs landscapes and ascents. Doing this will train your cardio and muscles to be prepared for those more challenging stages. Study up The Giro is well worth studying before undertaking. It is replete with stunning mountain passes and hairpin turns in abundance, something which can be quite challenging for those who didn‚Äôt take the time to properly estimate the ride‚Äôs significance. Study up before taking on the tour so that you know exactly what your body has to be prepared for as well as how to organise your training sessions. Eat after training Eating after any form of training is important for refuelling your body and cycling is no exception. It‚Äôs imperative to eat at least half an hour after training as this provides your body with the nutrients it needs to properly recover and have your body ready for further training. The same goes for when you are on the tour itself. Eating on the tour It‚Äôs vital for any cyclist mid-tour to eat a healthy, nutritious breakfast before starting out. Whilst it may be tempting to launch into the abundance of breads that are an Italian breakfast staple, these often will not provide you with the nutrients you need to effectively take on a stage. Stick to something light and nutritious ‚Äì fruits are recommended as well as breakfast smoothies to give you a much-needed morning energy boost. Enjoy yourself As an experienced cyclist, you will know that this is going to be one of the most rewarding life experiences you can undertake. And whilst it does take some work and dedication to prepare for, this is all just part of the incredible experience that is the Giro d‚ÄôItalia. ‚Ä¶ Where to go Camping in New South Wales? August 26, 2020 Tourism So, you‚Äôre planning to visit New South Wales for your next vacation? Well, you must consider bringing your camping equipment with you because NSW is best known for its camping spots. Most of the camping spots are popular worldwide but some camping spots are only popular among locals. So, if you‚Äôre willing to enjoy a relaxing experience, you must consult the locals to find the best camping spots. Fortunately, we‚Äôve prepared a list of some amazing spots where you can go camping in New South Wales. So, without wasting any time, let‚Äôs talk about what kind of experience you‚Äôd get in these spots. Honeymoon Bay, Jervis Bay If you‚Äôre willing to enjoy a bush camping experience, it‚Äôs the best spot for you. This campsite is located around 3 hours away from Sydney at the northern end of Jervis Bay. You‚Äôd get to explore some incredible beaches in this spot. The locals often visit this campsite during school holidays and even on weekends. You need to visit this campsite during the weekdays because this is how you can easily find a spot. There isn‚Äôt any gas cooking equipment available at this campsite. So, you must bring your equipment with you. Also, you must bring plenty of drinking water with you. Yuraygir National Park, Wooli Yuraygir National Park has a 65km of coastline where you can find the best beachside campsites. Make sure that you use a high-clearance 4WD for traveling because it gets difficult to go past the Pebbly Beach campground. That‚Äôs why these campsites aren‚Äôt mostly crowded by people. So, you can enjoy a comfortable and relaxing experience. You won‚Äôt even have to book a site before going there. Simply, bring your stuff with you and enjoy an incredible camping experience. Mimosa Rocks National Park It‚Äôs the best camping spot for those who like to travel in a caravan. You‚Äôd get to see some beautiful trees, rocks, and beaches in this tourist spot. You can go for a picnic or enjoy the coastal walks in this park. The reason why it‚Äôs an ideal spot for caravan travelers is that there isn‚Äôt any drinking water here. And you‚Äôre also supposed to bring the cooking equipment with you. And that can only happen if you have a bigger vehicle to store the equipment. You don‚Äôt need to bring an expensive caravan to have some fun in this picnic spot. A Retreat caravan would be enough for bringing the required equipment. If you don‚Äôt already have one, you can easily find Retreat Caravans for Sale from our friends at Freestyle RVs. So, load everything into the caravan and get ready to enjoy an incredible vacation‚Ä¶. Picture Perfect Day Trips to Take from Wanaka August 23, 2020 Tourism Wanaka is a favourite location for tourists and locals alike. From its snow-capped mountains to the famous Lake Wanaka, wacky attractions to a wilderness of glaciers ‚Äì it‚Äôs no surprise that we all keep coming back from more. If you‚Äôre thinking of visiting Wanaka or planning another trip to this truly unique spot, you may be wondering where else nearby you can venture to for a day trip. So, where are the best day trips just a short drive from Wanaka? Take a look below to find out. Mount Aspiring National Park A trip to Wanaka is not complete without a visit to Mount Aspiring National Park. This iconic park is renowned for being the most pristine and untouched national park in the country, with its beautiful mountain peaks and abundance of greenstone. If you want to make a quick trip through the park, you can take a short walk to the Blue Pools, where you can see deep pools of glacial blue water. This one-hour walking track will take you over cross swing bridges and boardwalks as you experience breathtaking views of the river gorge. If you are keen for a longer trip, you can hike the Rob Roy Glacier Track to experience the iconic landscape firsthand. Hikers can enjoy views of the Rob Roy glacier, stunning waterfalls and dramatic sheer rock cliffs as they take in all of the beauty that nature has to offer. Makarora Makarora is known for being a popular stop along the Haast Pass and for good reason. Known for its walking and hiking trails, breathtaking mountains and river valleys, it is no surprise that visitors never run out of things to do in Makarora. Lovers of unique experiences can enjoy a scenic helicopter ride above the mountains as they take in the views from new heights, flying above crystal clear lakes and snow-topped peaks. If you consider yourself an adrenaline junkie, why not take a ride on a jet boat and skim across the Wilkin and Makarora river? If you would prefer something more relaxing, there are plenty of hiking trails to choose from to get your nature fix. Siberia Valley is known for its beautiful native rainforest, stunning mountain vistas and crystal-clear streams, perfect for hikers of any level. Lake Hawea Located just a scenic 15-minute drive from Wanaka, you will find the beauty that is Lake Hawea. If you‚Äôre looking for somewhere to relax, this may be just the place ‚Äì with plenty of spots to kick back by the water as you take in the beautiful scenery. If you consider yourself more of a thrill seeker, there are plenty of activities on offer. Sportspeople rejoice ‚Äì at Lake Hawea, you can enjoy kite surfing, kayaking and boating surrounded by the stunning scenery that this location is renowned for. If you would like to take in the views with a hike, follow the trail from Timaru Creek as you wander through a beautiful, beech forest all the way to a braided riverbed. Cool off afterwards with a dip in Lake Hawea to complete your day trip!‚Ä¶ Our Road Trip Plan in NSW April 16, 2020 Tourism If you‚Äôre planning for a road trip to NSW, this article is really important for you. We‚Äôd be describing some of the amazing experiences we had while we were on a road trip in NSW. Without any doubt, NSW is the best place where you can explore amazing mountain ranges and valleys. And that‚Äôs not just it. You‚Äôd also get to explore a waterfall safari, beautiful farmlands, rock tunnels, and a few river crossings. So, without any delay, let‚Äôs take a look at how you can prepare a plan for a road trip in NSW. The Kosciuszko Alpine Way If you love exploring the mountain ranges, you must include the Alpine way into your list. You‚Äôd get to see the picturesque valleys in this beautiful range. There are many fishing stops where you can enjoy fishing at different levels. You can also give a try to mountain biking when you‚Äôre exploring this beautiful area. The walking trails give you the opportunity to explore this area from a completely different perspective. We recommend going to the Snowy Mountain regions through Kosciuszko National Park. This is the place where you can create some amazing memories with your friends and family members. Mollymook Drive We planned to visit Mollymook as well because there are many beautiful spots in this region. This area is best known for offering a seaside treat and we really enjoyed our visit to this beautiful spot. The reason why we went to this spot is that we like to capture the picturesque rolling hills and white fences. We also added plenty of photographs of different animals into our memory bank. The Waterfall Way How could we forget the Waterfall way when going on a road trip to NSW? We got the opportunity to explore national parks, lofty lookouts, lush rainforest, and amazing waterfall views during our trip. We had to go through some problems while traveling to the Waterfall way. My car broke down when we were leaving Sydney. So, I had to sell my car in Blacktown because we couldn‚Äôt wait for a week to get the car fixed. However, the rest of the journey was filled with a lot of fun and entertainment. And we‚Äôre never going to forget this amazing trip. Those, who are planning to take a road trip to NSW, must make all the preparations before time. This town is the perfect place for families that want to go for a day trip from Albury‚Ä¶. 5 Activities to do in Albury February 5, 2020 Tourism Going for an adventurous tour to Albury? So, without any delay, let‚Äôs take a look at the 5 activities you can do in Albury. Have Fun at Noreuil Park Noreuil Park is the hub of adventurous activities in Albury. It offers incredible places for kayaking, bike riding, paddle boarding, swimming, and relaxing on the riverbank. There are so many activities to enjoy that you won‚Äôt get bored even if you spend your entire day at this park. Usually, the people come for a day-long picnic to this park. Without any doubt, Noreuil Park is the best place where you can spend some quality time with your friends and family. Take a Visit to Murray River Murray River offers tons of fun and entertainment for visitors throughout the year. There are lots of reserves and parklands where you can enjoy the beauty of the river all-day-long. The Wagirra Trail offers an incredible view of Murray River when you ride a bike on it. Tucked away under the historic Parker & Parker building on Howard St, Andaluz opened in February 2009 and immediately stated its claim as one of Perth's premier small bars. The brainchild of husband and wife team Ryan Gregory & Carla Arevalo, Andaluz draws its inspiration from years of travel, research, hospitality experience from around the world and a touch of Spanish heritage. The result is a contemporary style bar which is both intimate and eclectic, mingling cosy antique leather lounges with beautiful soft furnishings. Andaluz offers a diverse range of Spanish & Australian wines & beers, an extensive list of classic & contemporary cocktails along with a huge selection of spirits to choose from. In the kitchen head chef Rick Welch produces an ever-changing menu of traditional and modern tapas all designed to be shared and enjoyed with friends. bookings Walk-ins always welcome, bookings are recommended for peak times if you are wanting to secure a table or lounge. Online bookings are only available for groups of 2 to 6 For groups over 6 please email us for availability. Groups of 8 or more will be classified as a function and minimum spends may apply. name: Gwydir Grill
homepage_content: Bingara - Gwydir Shire Council Skip to content Search for: Search for: Bingara vinkpub 2025-03-20T12:31:25+11:00 Bingara Bingara offers a perfect balance of peace and tranquillity while boasting an energetic and vibrant community. There‚Äôs always something happening; how much you choose to do is up to you, take life by the reins and explore all this hidden gem has to offer, or sit back and just go with the flow. Bingara, known as the ‚ÄúGem on the Gwydir‚Äù, is a great place to visit and an even better place to live. Safe and friendly, Bingara has clean air, clear skies and a great climate. Surrounded by rolling hills, the town rests in a natural amphitheatre. The spectacular Gwydir River is the life blood of the town, and its beauty is indeed priceless. History Bingara started life as a river crossing for teamsters travelling north, however it wasn‚Äôt until the 1880s when prospectors flocked to the area following the discovery of tin, then diamonds, that the town flourished, and rapid development followed. Bingara became a municipality in 1890 and at its peak, the main street alone boasted five general stores, six hotels, and all the services required to maintain a largely self-sufficient town. World economic recession and the end of mining saw the town contract, leaving a heritage of beautiful commercial and public architecture, and the now fully restored Roxy Theatre. Top things to do Bingara may be a small town by city standards, but there is no shortage of things to see and do, and it need not cost any money. 1. Fossicking The Bingara district is a fossickers paradise. Whichever road you take out of town you will find a spot to fossick for gold, gems and crystals. It was the discovery of gold in 1852 that brought a flow of prospectors to the district and it continues to this day. 2. ENTERTAINMENT Living in a country town does not mean that you have to live in a cultural void. On the contrary, residents of the Bingara district are privileged to have the arts firmly embroiled in their everyday lives. Art shows, cultural events and live theatre are the norm for the children of Bingara. 3. BUSH ACTIVITIES The picturesque river and mountains surrounding Bingara make it the ideal destination to discover the magic of the bush. You see it, you touch it, you live it. Whether you discover it by car or on foot all you need to do is look around and up, to experience the same as our ancestors. 4. Recreation There is no excuse for inactivity in Bingara, because the town has something for everyone. Whether you like to take a leisurely stroll or bike ride along the banks of the Gwydir River, throw in a fishing line, take a dip in the local swimming pool or prefer a more arduous climb up to Batterham Lookout, the choice is yours. 5. EXPLORING Using Bingara as a base, there are many delightful half and full-day drives which will take you into the hills, valleys and beyond. Whether your interest lies in geographical wonders unique to this area, or historical steps back in time, or whether you simply want a relaxing day out, we have it right here on our doorstep. name: Antonios Xpress
homepage_content: Antonio's Xpress - Berserker Order now About Us At Antonio's Xpress, we go beyond mere fast food. We're a celebration of family, an explosion of flavors, and a showcase of fresh ingredients zooming through our kitchen like a high-performance race car. We serve as the pit stop for those with hectic schedules who yearn for the comforting taste of homemade-quality Italian cuisine. However, we're not all about speed; we take the time to simmer our home-made sauces and we personally mix and roll our uniquely flavored pizza bases, fresh everyday, and slow-cook our ribs to absolute perfection. For us, fast food doesn't equate to compromising quality or flavor. At Antonio's, every dish is a warm embrace on a plate, and we ensure it reaches you in record time, making your dining experience truly irresistible. name: Bottles And Barrels
homepage_content: Home | BOTTLES & BARRELS top of page BOTTLES & BARRELS COFFEE | WINE | FOOD A Bit About Us Pop in to Bottles & Barrels wine store and caf√©. Our friendly establishment at 132 Aberdeen Street Geelong West, is where friends and family come together to enjoy great coffee, fine wine and wholesome food. Our coffee has the right amount of flavour and is served just the way you like it. Our wine is from far and near and you'll be sure to find just the right drop to suit. Our food includes great toasties, healthy salads, filling soups, fancy pies and there is always room for something sweet. We also offer take home meals for those who want a home cooked meal but don‚Äôt have the time. Our relaxed atmosphere offers a delightful escape for wine enthusiasts and coffee connoisseurs alike. So come join us, raise a glass and toast to good company, great food, and unforgettable memories. Cheers! COFFEE | WINE | FOOD Take Your Pick CAFE MENU SEVEN SEEDS COFFEE house made biscuits, muffins and slices fruit toast granola avocado & tomato with goats cheese on toast egg & bacon roll chicken & avo wrap reuben ham, cheese & tomato toasty mushroom toasty fresh chicken sandwich zucchini slice fresh daily soups take home meals ‚Äã ‚Äã ‚Äã WINE STORE CRAFT BEER & PRODUCE As lovers of a good drop, we have handpicked our favourite local wines including Lethbridge, Mazzini and Mermerus, then we‚Äôve added the very best from the regions that make them famous. For us it is Bollinger for Champagne, Peyurassol for Provence, Skillogalee for Clare Valley, Syrahmi for Heathcote just to name a few! We are also proud champions of local craft breweries with the advantage of stocking limited release beers, you'll always find something to tickle your fancy, if not just a little bit different. For traditionalists, we stock a range of the usual suspects as well to ensure everyone can find a beer at Bottles & Barrels. FUNCTIONS COCKTAIL & DINNER PARTIES At Bottles & Barrels we can cater for a variety of events or small. Our friendly establishment at 132 Aberdeen Street Geelong West, is where friends and family come together to enjoy great coffee, fine wine and wholesome food. Our coffee has the right amount of flavour and is served just the way you like it. Our wine is from far and near and you'll be sure to find just the right drop to suit. Our food includes great toasties, healthy salads, filling soups, fancy pies and there is always room for something sweet. We also offer take home meals for those who want a home cooked meal but don‚Äôt have the time. Our relaxed atmosphere offers a delightful escape for wine enthusiasts and coffee connoisseurs alike. So come join us, raise a glass and toast to good company, great food, and unforgettable memories. Cheers! For us it is Bollinger for Champagne, Peyurassol for Provence, Skillogalee for Clare Valley, Syrahmi for Heathcote just to name a few! name: Cairns Esplanade Lagoon
homepage_content: Cairns Esplanade | Cairns Regional Council Cairns Esplanade Share Facebook Send In Messenger Send In Messenger Twitter Email Esplanade Active Living free fitness classes Council offers eight free Active Living fitness classes along the Cairns Esplanade. The classes are suitable for all levels of fitness. Esplanade playgrounds The Esplanade features three playgrounds that encourage active play on the city's beautiful foreshore. Entry to all our playgrounds is free. Esplanade sport & fitness facilities There are many facilities to choose from along The Esplanade to suit your active lifestyle such as the Lagoon, Beach Volleyball Courts and fitness stations (green gyms). Esplanade BBQs There are a range of BBQ facilities and picnic areas along the Cairns Esplanade for your next event or gathering.The BBQs are free for casual use and are open from 6am to 9pm daily. Toilets, showers & parking Toilets, showers, lockers and parking are conveniently located along the Cairns Esplanade to make your visit more enjoyable. Commercial activities, photography & busking If you wish to use the Esplanade for a commercial (money making) activity, you may need a permit. Holding an event or celebration The Esplanade parklands are free for casual use. You can also hire the parklands for your next event. Public Art on the Esplanade There are many public artworks located along the Cairns Esplanade and by the Lagoon. Take a stroll along the Esplanade and you're bound to see one of these amazing pieces. Memorials on the Esplanade Cairns has a rich history which is highlighted in the memorials and monuments along the Cairns Esplanade foreshore. Taking your dog to the Esplanade Dogs are welcome on the Esplanade, but are not allowed in the Lagoon and the surrounding parklands, or within 2m of playgrounds and barbecues. Holding a peaceful assembly Information on holding a peaceful assembly on the Cairns Esplanade. name: Daisy√¢‚Ç¨‚Ñ¢s Place
homepage_content: Daisy's Place is Currently Closed Skip to content Daisy‚Äôs Place, located near the Caloundra turnoff on Steve Irwin Way in Glenview, stands as a testament to nearly a century of history. Originally built in 1923 as The Rustic Cabin by Master Builder Jess Samuel D. Johnson and his wife, Daisy Emma Johnson, the tea house quickly became a well-loved stop for weary travellers along what was then the Bruce Highway. Famous for its homemade pies and Devonshire teas, the Rustic Cabin was first located 100 meters north of its current site before being relocated in 1942 under a Queensland Forestry Lease. Tragedy struck the Johnson family when their daughter, Doris, drowned nearby in 1937, followed by Mr. Johnson‚Äôs passing in 1948. Despite these hardships, Daisy continued to run the establishment until her death in 1979. In 2010, former Mooloolah resident Sue Joseph, who had once worked at the Rustic Cabin, purchased the property and undertook extensive renovations to restore the termite-damaged structure. By mid-2011, the caf√© was reborn as Daisy‚Äôs Place, with Daisy Johnson‚Äôs former living quarters transformed into an intimate dining and reading space. Today, Daisy‚Äôs Place remains a cherished part of the Sunshine Coast‚Äôs history, surrounded by the scenic Jowarra Interpretive Forest Walk, which offers visitors a glimpse into the area‚Äôs natural beauty alongside its rich past. To get in touch: sue@suejoseph.com

name: Flavour of India Edgecliff
homepage_content: Flavour of India About Us We delight in knowing you come back to us time and time again. After over 20 years, this means an enormous amount. The History Flavour of India is a proud restaurant institution in Sydney, and our menu captures flavours and cooking styles from every corner of the beautiful continent that is India. We have a committed long standing team along with a few new faces. Our acclaimed head chef Hayat, has been here from day one and his team in the kitchen average 12 years of service. Hayat's philosophy as a head chef is that if your team is happy, calm & energetic, from that good food full of love will come. Bevan & Christine Neale, old friends of the original owner Lola Crossingham, are now at the helm, with a floor team dedicated to ensuring you have a fabulous experience, many of whom have been serving you for years already. Our drivers are a character filled bunch, driving all over the eastern suburbs and racing each other, to be the most speedy driver (within the boundaries of the law of course) of the night! We love feeding people. Our local clientele, our hollywood A-lister regulars (they like Indian food too!) and our tourists on a good tip off are all always welcome and we have a few exciting surprises in stall for you all. Opening Hours Call For Reservations Open Every Day 06:00pm 10:00pm RESERVATION NUMBER: 02-9326-2659 | LOCATION: 128 New South Head Road, Edgecliff Menu Entrees Bombay Rolls 3pc Crispy wrapped roll filled with lamb, potato, onion, peas, garlic, ginger, cumin, and corriander, served with two sauces mint & Tamarind. Samosas 2pc Many local diners have claimed ours is the best. Deep fried patties stuffed with fresh potatoes, green peas and freshly grounded Indian spices, served with minted yoghurt. Spicy crab (kakra thal) Crab meat in shredded ginger, chilli & onion, served inside potato skins. Tandoor Charcoal Sizzling Platter A mixed platter of melting tandoori lamb cutlets, chicken tikka fillets & tandoori fish fillets served on a sizzling plate served with vegetable (two of each per serve). Exotic chicken salad Warm tandoori fillets tossed with mango, avocado, diced tomatoes & salad greens with a light yoghurt dressing. Vegetable Palek paneer Our home made Indian style cheese with spinach leaves, fresh tomato and onion. Shahi Bagun Eggplant, lime leaves, ginger, chashew nut paste, coconut oil, light cream light curry. Malai kofta Crushed paneer, potato, cashew balls, deep fried & served in a rich creamy sauce. Chicken Best Chicken Butter Masala Our specialty. chicken from the tandoor served in our creamy red masala sauce Chicken jalfrezi A spice mix of cinnamon, cardamom & clove form the base of this fragrant curry with fresh garlic and ginger along with tomato, curry leaves, dry chilli & coriander. Chicken hayat Created by our chef Hayat. Chicken pieces, potato & snow peas cooked in a delicious light sauce. Beef, Lamb & Goat Kashmiri Beef A flavoursome Kashmiri dish with ginger, garlic, a touch of tomato and our in-house blended garam masala, simmered with cream and yoghurt on slow heat. Lamb rogan josh A regional Kashmiri dish over 400 years old. Lamb pieces seared and braised in a host of spices with capsicum & methi leaves, then slow cooked into a melting texture. Goat Curry Be adventurous and go for the goat curry. The tender, goat meat is saute√å¬Åed in spices then slow cooked with onions, garlic and potatoes until it falls off the bone. Seafood Green Fish Curry Another southern Indian dish, this curry contains fillets of fish in a sauce of tamarind, coconut, green chilli & ginger. 5 Spice Garlic Prawns 24-hour marinade of garlic, onion and our 5-spice blend, finished with a simmer to order, touch of cream and fresh snow peas. Malabar Prawns A superb southern prawn dish heralding coconut oil & coconut cream, desiccated coconut, mustard seed & fresh lime leaves. Takeaway Menu Dine In Menu Drinks Menu Reservations Book a table with free & instant online restaurant reservations. Flavour of India Make a Reservation Open Hours All 7 Days a Week! 06:00pm - 10:00pm 02-9326-2659 Make a Booking Gallery If a picture says a thousand words, then you can imagine how long it would take to describe all our mouthwatering selections. Testimonials √¢¬Ä¬ù Great Food & Service Came here on a visit from the UK and happened to stumble across this restaurant as it was near our apartment. Food was fantastic, lots of vegetarian options and the service was great. The chef also gave us complimentary chocolate naan which is a must! Charlotte F Tasty Food & Great Service Got there right when it opened at 6. Able to order quickly and food came out promptly. Got a huge meal which we managed to finish because everything was so delicious. Samosas to start: two tasty fried potato dumplings. Then cheese and garlic naan: I had never had this and it was a culinary experience. Unbelievably tasty. Chicken Tikka masala: way above average. Lamb rogan josh: best I have ever had. Chet P Home Away from Home! Visited our first Indian restaurant in Australia and I must say it lived up to the reviews !! The food was lovely, but the stand out factor was the great service from the chef himself. A lovely man with a huge heart, walking round and having conversations with all his guests. Me and my partner thought it reminded us of a curry house local to our home in London. A home away from home! Harry L Top -->

name: Fresh Thailicious Delights
homepage_content: Thai Food catering Rockhampton | Fresh Thailicious Delights CALL US NOW!!! 0432 148 242 Food So Good You Can Taste It SCROLL DOWN THAI FOOD AND CATERING SERVICE IN CENTRAL QUEENSLAND At Fresh Thailicious Delights we ensure your private or corporate event is a culinary success. Sourcing the freshest local produce available, our chefs prepare authentic Thai cuisine for clients throughout Central Queensland. Arriving on time with our purpose-built food truck, your guests will be treated to a wide selection of dishes that are infused with the exotic flavours and aromas of traditional Thai cuisine. We all love food. But what separates good food from great food is the combination of high-quality produce and preparation by experienced hands. At Fresh Thailicious Delights, we are proud to provide Thai food that looks good, tastes great and is also value for money. With your direction, our chefs create a menu that's tailored to suit your occasion. We understand that planning an event can be stressful. But with the help of our expert team, the food side of it will be handled with ease. Looking for a unique catering experience? Contact us today to book one of our affordable package deals. We service the entire Central Queensland region, as well as surrounding areas on special request. *Vegetarian and gluten-free dishes are available. PRIVATE EVENTS Make your birthday, wedding or private event memorable with a spread of delectable authentic Thai cuisine. CORPORATE FUNCTIONS We provide scrumptious Thai dishes for corporate lunches, functions, expos and more. FESTIVALS & MARKETS Our authentic Thai cuisine is the perfect crowd-pleaser at any festival, market or large-scale event. TESTIMONIALS Thailicious worked with us to design a menu that suited our style of wedding, and all the needs of our guests‚Äîgluten-free, and vegetarian. Their service was seamless and there was more than enough food. It was spectacular. They even fed the bar staff and musicians. We would recommend them to you for sure. - Jess & Merv D. Very yummy food and friendly service. The best in the business. All our guests complimented the catering and they helped to complete our open-style backyard wedding. - Olivia & Dennis C. You guys were amazing! The food was fresh and flavoursome, and everybody loved it. Who'd of thought we could have exotic Thai food cooked and served in our backyard for 80 people. Thank you so much for coming to help make our special day. - Angie & Aaron H. Fresh Thailicious Delights delivered a Thai food banquet in the middle of Central Queensland Coal Country. Everything was perfect! Everyone commented on how good the food was, and there was plenty of it too‚Äîthat's important for Mining Management. We'll certainly have you back and recommend you within the industry! - Anglo American M. Thank you for the most wonderful food for our wedding. You were so easy to work with, it took so much stress of all the other planning we had to contend with. We love you guys. Thank you for coming way out of town to our family property and giving our family and guests something special. - Anna & Dan Thank you for providing the catering at our Annual AGM Dinner at The Haven. Everyone was very impressed with the meals and service. We will certainly recommend you to anyone looking for great food. - Emu Park L.-Dr Peter R. Thank you for the wonderful food for all our family and guests at our recent wedding anniversary celebrations. To have you come to our home and serve us with gorgeous food was tremendous. We greatly appreciate the care you afforded us in planning for the celebrations, it helped make things run smoothly on the evening. - Lauren & George B. Being gluten intolerant, sometimes I struggle to find anything different and healthy to eat. Thank you Thailicious, I will be a frequent flyer at your store and Tan, thank you for the specially made gluten-free dishes. - Sally-Louise J. These guys catered for our wedding at Henderson Park and it was amazing food! They were so friendly and professional and worked to understand our needs all along the way. The food was cooked fresh and served ready to eat, and there was plenty to go around. We even had leftovers for the following day's breakfast. Love you guys! - Alisha & Dean B. ABOUT US Fresh Thailicious Delights is your private, commercial and corporate catering expert. Preparing handmade, authentic Thai cuisine from our purpose-built food truck, our chefs provide catering for weddings, birthday parties, large-scale festivals and more. name: Fortnums Restaurant & Wedding Venue
homepage_content: Fortnums Restaurant | Wedding Reception Venue | Functions | Dandenong Ranges Home Restaurant Menu Lunch Menu Dessert Menu Wine Menu Gluten Free Menu Mothers Day Menu Christmas in July Menu Weddings Functions Private Function Garden Room High Tea Contact Picnics and Platters 03 9755 1200 Online Shop Home Restaurant Menu Lunch Menu Dessert Menu Wine Menu Gluten Free Menu Mothers Day Menu Christmas in July Menu Weddings Functions Private Function Garden Room High Tea Contact Picnics and Platters Fortnums Restaurant, Weddings & Functions Venue Restaurant & Wedding Reception Venue Dandenong Ranges Fortnums is set in the heart of the beautiful Dandenong Ranges, in the quaint village of Sassafras, a short drive from iconic attractions such as Puffing Billy and the Rhododendron Gardens. Fortnums overlooks the spectacular nearby ranges and is set amongst picturesque gardens. Fortnums has the bright airy look and feel of an English conservatory with a charming atmosphere created by warm friendly staff and relaxing music. Our menu draws its inspiration from a variety of good honest comfort food and modern Australian cuisine. We are known near and far for our high quality lunch, desserts and High Teas, not to forget our famous traditional scones served with a variety of jams and conserves all made on our premises. We serve a selection of local wines from the Yarra Valley and other Australian regions, and also stock a wide variety of local and imported beers and spirits. Fortnums is open almost every week of the year, Wednesday to Sunday 11:00am to 4:00pm, and we welcome bookings and enquiries . Fortnums can also cater for small and large group bookings and can create a set menu to suit your taste and budget. Dining in the restaurant or our private garden room overlooking our garden and Melbourne's skyline. If you are planning a birthday, an event or that very special day, your wedding, fortnums can offer itself as the premier boutique wedding and function Venue in the Dandenongs. Call us on 03 9755 1200 Fortnums News Christmas in July! Its that time of the year again! At Fortnums we love Christmas so much that we do it twice a year! Come and join us for our famous Christmas 2 or 3 course lunch, served every day we are open. Please click this link to see our menu. No, we aren‚Äôt talking about those big moments you see in photo albums years later, but the ones that happen in-between; the ones you remember. You see, we like to think good coffee has the ability to bring people together and slow life down for a minute, so that you can hatch your next adventure.
