Mount Fuji Guided Day Tour with Kachikachi Ropeway & Matcha-Making Experience ‚Äå ‚Äå Japan is well known for a number of things ‚Äî sushi, tea ceremonies, kimonos, ninjas, anime, manga, and most importantly, cherry blossoms. The very word Japan conjures images of Mount Fuji surrounded by the pink flowers. The sakura (Japanese for ‚Äòcherry blossom‚Äô) symbolizes mortality ‚Äî the fleeting nature of life; it reminds us of how something so beautiful can also be short. The cherry blossom reminds us to live every day to the fullest. Here are some Japan cherry blossom tours you can take to experience the graceful beauty of nature, while making the most of life. Cherry Blossom in Japan Cherry blossoms are a symbol of high importance in Japan, so much so that the flower is even featured on the 100 yen coin. The flower reaches full bloom in spring, which is when visitors flock to popular spots around the city to view these blossoms from and have a picnic under the blanket of these blushing petals. Spring typically is a bit chilly in Japan, with temperatures reaching an average of 12¬∞C in March and about 17¬∞C in April. However, the mornings and nights are especially chilly, with northern parts of Japan such as Hokkaido being especially cold. Hence, it is advised that when you are packing for your cherry blossom tour in Japan, carry along sweaters as well in case it is cold. When is the Cherry Blossom Season in Japan 2021? Cherry blossom season in Japan typically starts around March and goes on till the end of April. The northern parts of the country, such as Hokkaido, typically experience cherry blossom season much later ‚Äî around May. In some cases, the season starts in February for slow blooming cherry blossom varieties like the Kawazuzakura (found in the city of Kawazu in Izu Peninsula) and the Atamizakura (found in the city of Atami, in Shizuoka perfecture). During this time, you can take a cherry blossom tour in Japan and check out the numerous cherry blossom festivals across the country that take place specifically around this time. The following is a rough approximation of when cherry blossom season starts across the different cities in Japan: Late February: Kawazu, Atami City Early March: Matsuda Mid-March: Minamiashigara City Late March: Fukuoka, Hiroshima, Matsuyama, Tokyo Early April: Kyoto, Nagoya, Nara, Osaka Mid-April: Fuji, Fukushima, Kanazawa, Sendai Late April: Aomori, Hakodate, Hirosaki Early May: Sapporo Cherry Blossoms in Japan See all photos Japan Cherry Blossom Tour 2021 Locations Atami City : Home to the lovely cherry blossom variety Atamizakura, Atami city is a two-hour drive from Tokyo. The flowers bloom between January and February, with the last four years seeing the flowers start blooming by February. Matsuda : A beautiful town located in Kanagawa Prefecture, Matsuda sees its cherry blossoms bloom between February and March. You can also find the Kawazuzakura variety here, especially during the Matsuda Cherry Blossom Festival, which is typically held in February. Minamiashigara City : Located in Kanagawa Prefecture, Minamiashigara City typically sees its cherry blossoms start to bloom in March. During this time, the riverbank, which is surrounded by over 150 cherry trees blooms together, creating a large pink canopy. Tokyo : The capital city sees cherry blossoms start to bloom mid-March and reach full bloom by the end of the month. This magical experience is best enjoyed by strolling down Chidorigafuchi and munching on cherry blossom-flavoured snacks. Jinroku Sakura Park : Featuring over 40 varieties of cherry blossom trees, this massive park is perfect for those who want to see the different species in one place. It is home to the famous Kawazuzakura, Jugatsuzakura, and Somei Yoshino. Why Take a Cherry Blossom Tour The sakura (cherry blossom) is a flower of high importance in Japan. A symbol of transience, it is a reminder of the impermanence of life. To look at the beautiful pink canopy surrounding you may make you feel wistful, but is also an inspiration to enjoy every single minute. The cherry blossoms only appear for about a month, so this time is filled with lots of revelry. Many people get together to indulge in hanami (cherry blossom viewing) with picnics or by attending sakura-themed festivals. A cherry blossom tour in Japan takes you to different places in the country from where you can admire the raw beauty of nature with a beautiful pink hue. To admire these delicate flowers is a peaceful experience in its own right. Types of Cherry Blossom Tours Guided Tours A guided tour involves a professional English-speaking guide who tells you everything there is to know about cherry blossom season and takes you to places to get the best view of it. Transfers are usually covered as part of a guided tour, ensuring a hassle-free visit. Combo Tours A combo cherry blossom tour combines visiting the cherry blossoms along with other landmarks or experiences like Mishima Skywalk, Shiraito Falls, Fujisan Sengen Shrine, and Mount Fuji‚Äôs fifth station. Transportation and a guide are usually included for a stress-free visit. Which Cherry Blossom Tour Should You Take? Budget-friendly For those looking for a cherry blossom tour that is easy on the pocket, it is best to pick the non-guided or self-guided tour option. This way, you can pick a transport option that‚Äôs inexpensive and plan your trip as per your convenience, and including only the sights that you want to explore. Informative Apart from just admiring the cherry blossoms, if you also want to learn more about the history of the region and the importance and symbolism of cherry blossoms, pick a guided tour. While these are a touch more expensive, it is well worth the money, as it also includes transportation. Explorative If you are interested in what‚Äôs beyond the cherry blossoms, take a combo tour. As part of this, you can visit the Mount Fuji World Heritage Center, Shiriato Falls, Lake Ashi, Fujisan Sengen Shrine, Hakone-en, and Komagatake. Transfers, an English-speaking guide, and lunch are usually included. What to See In & Around Shizuoka Perfecture Shizuoka Prefecture is about three hours away from Tokyo, and offers some of the best cherry blossom-viewing opportunities. It is also home to Kawazu, Izu Peninsula, which is known for local cherry blossom species, Kawazukzakura, which typically has a longer life than most of the other species. When you go to see the Kawazuzakura, here are some other things you can do in and around Shizuoka Prefecture. Mishima Skywalk : The longest suspension bridge in Japan at 400m, the Mishima Skywalk gives you unbeatable views of Mount Fuji. You can also go ziplining for 300m as you look at the lofty peak. During winter, you can also get a spectacular view of the sunset. Mount Fuji World Heritage Center : Marking the designation of Mount Fuji as a UNESCO World Heritage Site, this attraction is designed to reflect the structure of the volcano in the pond outside. It also gives you insight into the history and cultural importance of the volcano, along with a stunning view of it. Arakurayama Sengen Park : Home to the Arakura Fuji Sengen-jinja Shrine and pagoda, the park is covered in a lovely pink canopy when cherry blossom season hits. Visitors are also afforded an amazing view of Mount Fuji in all its glory, especially on a clear day. Shiraito Falls : This plunging waterfall (at a height of 150m) gets its water directly from Mount Fuji, and is often referred to as the most beautiful waterfall in Japan. Located within the Fuji-Hakone-Izu National Park, it is surrounded by verdant trees. Its sheer beauty makes you feel connected to nature. Lake Ashi: Take in the stunning views of Mount Fuji as you take a boat cruise atop the sapphire waters of Lake Ashi. You can also see the striking red torii to the Hakone Shrine. During spring, the area is surrounded by cherry blossoms, creating an incredibly magical experience. Mount Fuji Fifth Station : The fifth (and last) station on the southern slope of Mount Fuji, this is the closest station to the summit. Visitors often start the hike to the peak of Mount Fuji from here, taking about 4-8 hours for the ascent. As the highest station on this route, it also gives you an awe-inspiring view of the volcano. Plan Your Visit Best time to visit Food & drinks Stay Shopping Must Do The best time to visit and admire the cherry blossoms is between March and April. It is within this period that the flowers‚Äô bloom cycle takes place. While the Kawazu cherry blossoms starts blooming earlier (around February), they only bloom fully by March. When admiring the cherry blossoms, try out cherry blossom-flavoured food such as: Sakura mochi: A traditional sweet flavoured with salted cherry blossom petals. Sakura yokan: Another traditional Japanese sweet, it consists of jellied sakura-an paste. Sakura macarons and cakes: These western dishes are reimagined with the unconventional, yet delicious cherry blossom. Sakura sake: This sakura-flavoured rice wine emits a delicate fragrance and tastes just as subtle. Sakura cha / Sakura yu: Enjoy sakura-flavoured tea, made with cherry blossoms pickled in salt. There are numerous accommodation options available in Tokyo, which is typically where most tourists stay and see the cherry blossoms at. Additionally, Tokyo is close to the Shizuoka prefecture, which is where a lot of people head to see the Kawazuzakura. It is recommended that you stay in Shinjuku when in Tokyo. Not only is it one of the best places to stay in the city, with a lot of different accommodation options, it is also close to Shinjuku station, which has great connectivity to the rest of the region. Other great places to stay at include Ginza, Hamamatsucho, Hibiya, Roppongi, Shibuya, and Shinagawa. Tokyo is a large city, so ensure wherever you stay is close to a subway or railway station for easy access. During cherry blossom season, one will find a number of cherry blossom-themed souvenirs and limited edition products to purchase. Starbucks rolls out sakura-themed tumblers and mugs, and Kit-Kat, Coca Cola, and Pepsi release sakura-flavoured products. Other sakura-themed things you can purchase include kokeshi dolls, pens, chopsticks, bento boxes, stationary, sweets, tea, accessories, and jewellery. Here are some attractions to visit and experiences to enjoy when visiting Japan to see the cherry blossoms bloom: Enjoy hanami (cherry blossom viewing) picnic under the beautiful canopy of sakura trees. Gorge on sakura-flavoured foods and drinks. Explore Izu Peninsula and admire the Kawazuzakura cherry blossoms. Head to Mount Fuji Five Stations to look at the stunning scenery. Visit the plunging Shiraito Falls. Go strawberry picking. Indulge in a traditional tea ceremony under the lovely cherry trees. Visitor Tips While there are many different types of cherry blossoms that bloom at different times of the year, the most famous is the Kawazuzakura, which blooms in the Shizuoka Prefecture. It typically starts to bloom by the end of February, so plan your trip to Japan at a time when you can view these cherry blossoms. The Izu Peninsula, home of Kawazuzakura, also hosts an annual Kawazu Cherry Blossom Festival , where you can try street food, buy souvenirs, and enjoy the beautiful flowers. The festival is scheduled to begin on February 10, 2021, but the date may change. If you want to check out cherry blossoms in the cities, Tokyo and Kyoto offer the best views. Note that these cherry blossoms only bloom for a fortnight. But for an unbeatable view, take a day trip to Shizuoka Prefecture and see the cherry blossoms framing the mighty Mount Fuji. Stay safe by keeping your mask on at all times and carrying your own hand sanitizer. Spring in Japan tends to be a little chilly, so carry along a light jacket. Be prepared to share this experience with thousands of people, as the blooming of the cherry blossoms is a magical sight that many people want to admire. Some of the best places to admire the cherry blossoms across the country include Kawazu, Izu Peninsula; Ueno Park and Chidorigafuchi in Tokyo; Philosopher‚Äôs Path and Maruyama Park in Kyoto; Kema Sakuranomiya Park and Osaka Castle in Osaka; and Nara Park in Nara. All Your Questions About Cherry Blossom Tours Answered Are cherry blossom tour tickets available online? Yes, cherry blossom tour tickets can be purchased online. It is actually recommended that you purchase your cherry blossom tour tickets online and in advance to secure your visit on the day of your preference. Can I take a guided Japan cherry blossom tour? Yes. There are several guided cherry blossom tours from Tokyo that take you to different parts of the country to see the flowers in full bloom. What is the best day tour from Tokyo to see cherry blossoms? The best day tours are combo tours as they include a variety of other experiences such as strawberry picking, ziplining, and the Mishima Skywalk. Whatare the ticket options available for Japanese cherry blossom tours? You can take your pick from a wide range of options, such as guided tours, park entry tickets (non-guided), and combo tours. The benefit offered by guided and combo tours is an English-speaking guide and the inclusion of transfers in your ticket. Combo tours, in addition, take you to more experiences in the surrounding area after the cherry blossom viewing. What happens if I need to cancel my Japan cherry blossom tour tickets? This depends on the tour ‚Äî some allow you to cancel 24 hours in advance, some require a week‚Äôs notice, and some cannot be cancelled or rescheduled. It is highly advisable to check the cancellation policy before booking your tickets. How long are my Japan cherry blossom tour tickets valid for? Your cherry blossom Japan tour tickets are valid for the date selected when booking the ticket. Should I purchase my tickets to see cherry blossoms in advance? It is recommended that you purchase your cherry blossom tour tickets in advance to get the date of your choosing. What language is the Japan cherry blossom guided tour conducted in? Guided cherry blossom tours in Japan are typically conducted in English. When does the cherry blossom season in Japan start? The best time to see cherry blossoms is during the bloom season, which falls between March and April. How long does a cherry blossom tour in Japan take? While this depends on the tour chosen, an average cherry blossom tour from Tokyo takes about half a day (12 hours) including transfer time. homepage_content: Daark Espresso - Chirn Park Speciality Coffee Pioneers Locally Sourced x Brewed With Love Table Service Venue. we are doing table service. to be seated, wait at the front. Embrace the dark side with Daark Espresso Daark is an espresso bar celebrated for its exceptional coffee, warm service and standout food ‚Äî and judging by the regular queue for a table, it‚Äôs clearly a local favourite. When you're on the hunt for the best breakfast in Southport, Daark is well worth the extra few minutes‚Äô drive. A true institution among seasoned brunch-goers, it's always buzzing with coffee lovers soaking up the relaxed vibe from the wrap-around deck. With full table service, we kindly ask that guests wait at the bottom of the stairs to be seated ‚Äî our team will get you settled as soon as possible. From Sweet Potato and Feta Fritters to Turkish Eggs and Lamb Salad, the menu offers a delicious variety for breakfast and lunch, all paired with award-winning Supreme Roasters coffee. You‚Äôll also find treats like our Biscoff latte, a rotating selection of matchas (including strawberry, blackberry and classic ceremonial etc..) and a full drinks lineup to suit every mood..Oh ‚Äî and don‚Äôt forget the homemade vanilla cold foam that makes every drink just that little bit better. Trust us. Tucked away in the charming pocket of Chirn Park on the Northern Gold Coast, Daark is open seven days for dine-in and takeaway specialty coffee, with all-day breakfast, lunch, beer, wine and cocktails. And if you‚Äôre struggling to leave your cosy bed, we‚Äôve got you covered ‚Äî literally. We provide warm woolly wraps to snuggle into while you dine alfresco. Drop by for a coffee or something chilled and see if you can resist the lure of our house-made French toast or crispy hash browns. Email Address Sign Up We respect your privacy. Thank you! Book a table for 4 or more Call Us : You can also book a table by calling or texting us directly at 0450 988 899 during our opening times. (05.30am - 02.30pm) Booking Policy : Note: We don‚Äôt take Bookings on Public Holidays or the Gold Coast Marathon Weekend. We accept reservations for groups of 4 to 10 people. No same Day Bookings We hold the table for 15 minutes past your reservation time. If you do not show up within this time, the table may be given to another customer. Tables are reserved for 1.5 hours. If you wish to stay longer, please let us know when you book the table. We look forward to serving you! Contact Us Please complete the form below No bookings enquiries via email. Please call or text us (0450 988 899) for a booking. This helps cook it faster but strips the grain of its essential nutrients. Daawat Brown Basmati undergoes the unique HET process so it retains the grain's full Bran layer, natural taste and goodness. Daawat Brown Rice Shelf Life Advantage ‚Äì It doesn‚Äôt become rancid Most of the commonly available Brown Rice becomes rancid after 3-4 months. The rice oil present in the Bran gets rancid due to activity of an enzyme called Lipase. Due to this fact some Brown rice may get rancid even before it reaches to consumer. When you buy Daawat Brown Rice you get the advantage of it staying fresh for minimum 24 months because we have the special technology to deactivate this Lipase enzyme so that it doesn‚Äôt become rancid. name: The Buoys Nelson Bay - Restaurant Cafe And Bar
homepage_content: The Buoys ‚Äî Flames and Flavour 0 BOOK A TABLE ONLINE Discover the vibrant atmosphere of The Buoys, located in the heart of the scenic Nelson Bay. Reflecting the spirit of this beautiful coastal haven, our venue invites you to enjoy a fresh and flavorful dining experience. With a focus on seasonally inspired dishes, we take pride in using locally-sourced ingredients to create meals that celebrate the best of the region. Whether you're stopping by for breakfast, lunch, or dinner, The Buoys offers a warm and inviting space to relax and savor the flavors of Nelson Bay. VIEW OUR MENU BUY A GIFTCARD BOOK A TABLE ONLINE CONTACT: (02) 4981 9392 Breakfast Lunch Dinner Wines Cocktails Location / Current Trading Hours Location: Shop No. 3/22 Yacaaba St, Nelson Bay NSW 2315 Opening Hours: Monday to Thursday from 11:30am ‚Äì 8:30pm Friday to Sunday from 7am ‚Äì 8:30pm Follow us on socials Instagram: @ thebuoysnelsonbay Facebook: The Buoys Nelson Bay Sarah Edwards ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ 5 stars 31 reviews ¬∑ 8 photos Aug 2024 Dine in | Brunch Impressive. This boutique cafe has just re-opened with new owners. First impressions - wow ! The cafe itself is warm, welcoming and clean. Tables are of generous size and spaced out, so you don‚Äôt feel like you‚Äôre sitting on top of everyone. There is an outdoor setting, with lights and high table and chairs in an alfresco setting. There is soft background music playing throughout the cafe. Menu offers a great variety and is all very reasonable priced. As a coffee snob, their coffee is 5/5 - better than anywhere else I‚Äôve tried in the bay. We met with the owner, Sanjay who is extremely friendly and welcoming. Taking the time to show us his cafe and explaining his plans for the future. Olivia was our waitress. She was also friendly, polite and had a smile of her face the whole time. She gave us space to read through the menu before coming back and taking our orders. A must cafe to visit. We had breakfast and will definitely be back for dinner. Food : 5/5 | Service : 5/5 | Atmosphere : 5/5 info@Flamesandflavourgroup.com.au Flames and Flavour Group Pty Ltd Restaurants are located in NSW, Australia: The General Roberts: (02) 4957 1818 258 Lambton Road, New Lambton, 2305 The Hamilton Station Hotel: (02) 4961 3852 2-6 Beaumont Street, Islington, 2296, The Buoys: (02) 4981 9392 Shop No. 3/22 Yacaaba St, Nelson Bay, 2315 Tilligerry RSL : (02) 4982 3889 Lemon Tree Passage Rd, Tanilba Bay NSW 2319

name: Kappo
homepage_content: Fumiki's ÈÆ®Ââ≤ÁÉπ„Åµ„Åø„Åç | Fine Dining Kaiseki/Sushi Restaurant | Shop 6/17 Barrett Street, Robertson Queensland, Australia top of page Restaurant Concept KyoKaiseki is Kaiseki cuisine served in Kyoto at high-end restaurants. Edomae sushi is the simple yet elegant sushi originated from Tokyo. Fumiki's Sushi Kappo combines these two luxurious traditional cuisines and serve them over the counter. Our omakase menu changes seasonally: the temperature, texture, flavour, presentation, plates and sequence of dishes are carefully orchestrated to give the best overall dining experience possible. With around 18 dishes of Omakase style course, guests can experience true Japanese fine-dining created by our chef Fumiki who has 30+ years of extensive experience across some of the best Japanese restaurants in Melbourne, Brisbane and Kyoto. ‚ÄãÂÖ´ÂØ∏ Chef's Profile Chef Fumiki Restaurants Experience: Akaiito Melbourne, Show Kitchen Head Chef Tsuru Melbourne, Consultant Chef Izakaya Kuuraku Melbourne, Head Sushi Chef Akachochin Melbourne, Head Chef Sumiya Ryokan Kyoto Japan, Chef Nobu at Crown Resorts Melbourne, Sushi Chef Koko at Crown Resorts Melbourne, Sushi Specialist Shoya Melbourne, Head Sushi Chef Sake Hamer Hall Melbourne, Head Sushi Chef Sono Brisbane, Executive Chef Oshin Brisbane, Head Sushi Chef Hilton Hotel Brisbane, Chef De Cuisine (Japanese) Kabuki at Stamford Plaza Hotel Brisbane, Japanese Chef De Partie Miyako Melbourne, Sushi Chef De Partie Murasaki Melbourne, Chef De Partie Terms & Conditions *Please read all terms & conditions before you make reservations. ‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã $285 per person ( not including drinks) for standard omakase course, $335 per person (not including drinks) for deluxe course. 10% weekend surcharge We require $140 deposit per person for standard course and $160 for deluxe course, via bank transfer within 6 hours at the agreed time of booking as booking congestion may accumulate. Please include your last name, number of people, date of booking in your reference. Once we have confirmed your payment, we will send you a confirmation via email. One session only from 6:30 PM - 9:30 PM (approx.) To ensure best possible quality dining experience of our patrons, we do not cater for children under the age of 12 inclusive. Should you turn up with children aged 12 or under on the day of your booking we reserve the right to cancel your booking on the spot and will not refund the deposit. We DO NOT cater for allergy to seafood, shellfish(including prawn, lobster, scampi, oyster, clams etc) , gluten-free, as most of the courses are seafood ingredients which are carefully selected for the best experience possible. If you do not eat raw fish then Fumiki‚Äôs might not be the place for you as we specialise in Edo-mae style sushi and sashimi. Ingredients are ordered according to the bookings, if there are changes to your booking you must inform us at least 3 days prior to your booking date to receive full refund. If cancellation occurs within 3 days of your booking date, deposit will be non-refundable to cover cost of ingredients. On the day of booking if the number of people is less than booked, the deposit cannot be used as discount or as credit towards food or beverage, it will be non-refundable as if cancellation was made within 3 days of your booking. ‚Äã To ensure a pleasant dining experience and due respect for all patrons, we ask that you arrive on time as we serve the food latest from 6:45 PM, earlier when all patrons arrive. Courses only, no a la carte. Restaurant Rules Smart Casual attire required, No Shorts, No sandals or thongs. Should you turn up with inappropriate attire, we reserve the right to refuse entry at the door. No strong fragrance or perfume, as this can interfere with your dining experience. Silent mode on all phones to ensure dining experiences for others. For food safety reasons, we do not offer take away services. To ensure the dining experience of our patrons we do not allow the use of camera flashes and intense lighting equipment. BYO is not allowed Contact Shop 6, 17 Barrett Street Robertson Qld 4109 info@fumikis.com.au Deposit and screenshot are essential to secure bookings. Please read terms and conditions. ‚Äã for single seat reservation please inquire by email as it may not show on website. ‚Äã Deluxe course upgrade items: ‚Äã Available Optional Item: ‚Äã ÔºàPlease noteÔºâ Upgrade ingredients are subject to availability and change without notice when sold out. Seat Reservation **10% Surcharge applies on Saturdays and Sundays. bottom of page

LEARN MORE Training & Employment Mining Industry & Others GreenGlass provides ongoing training and skills development for our employees working towards Certificate III level qualifications primarily in Plant operations and/or Resources and infrastructure. LEARN MORE GreenGlass We have been operational since 2009, and are based in Alice Springs. GreenGlass Trading was established to identify opportunities for Aboriginal employment throughout the Northern Australia and now works across a range of industry sectors, with a specific focus on developing the employability of individuals within a commercial setting. In more recent years GreenGlass has broadened its scope to include a number of other contracts including transport, cleaning and maintenance. name: Danosi Kitchen
homepage_content: Japanese Cooking Class | HERO COOKING | Gold Coast top of page Can't go to Japan? I will bring Japan to you! Healthy Tasty Authentic Japanese Cooking Classes ‚Äã Now available! Gift Voucher Gift Voucher Give an unforgettable experience to your friends, family or loved ones for a special occasion like birthdays, anniversaries or celebrations. ‚Äã Online purchase & delivery: Simply click the button below to purchase a Japanese Cooking Class Gold Coast voucher. I will send you a digital voucher upon receipt of payment. PURCHASE GIFT VOUCHER Learn to cook authentic Japanese food You may know Sushi, Ramen, Teppanyaki, but there is so much more amazing Japanese food! Japanese cuisine has been declared Intangible Cultural Heritage and travelers to Japan have been able to taste the large range of yummy Japanese meals. Now you can enjoy your favorite dishes without having to leave your home. Book a cooking class with me and I will come to your house to teach you how to cook authentic Japanese food! I will bring all ingredients and any special utensils from Japan with me when I come to your house (Gold Coast & Tweed Coast area). Let me share our country's passion for food with you and create a wonderful experience together! AVAILABLE JAPANESE COOKING CLASSES Browse through the classes below, whet your appetite and book your class online! ‚Äã When you participate in a class, you will receive: - Hands-on tutoring - Knowledge of common Japanese ingredients & cooking practices - Cooking lesson in English / Japanese - Lunch that you created - Recipe cards for the dishes - Shopping list that helps you find the ingredients at your local Japanese / Asian store - Name tag written in calligraphy - Surprise dessert FAMILY & PARTY CLASSES VIEW PREMIUM CLASSES VIEW MASTER CLASS VIEW Wear a traditional Japanese Yukata while cooking Special experience highly liked by previous customers! Wear a traditional Japanese casual Kimono (Yukata) while taking your class. I will show you how to dress up and you can take photos while cooking and outside with some scenery. LEARN MORE ABOUT YUKATA ABOUT HIRO I was born in Shiga, just a few minutes away from Kyoto, Japan. My village is surrounded by mountains and the biggest lake in Japan. My ancestors used to run a Ryokan (Japanese hotel), and I want to continue the tradition of giving Omotenashi (Japanese hospitality). My grandma and great grandma showed me how to cook traditional Japanese food, and my mum taught me how to make sweets. I moved to Australia in 2012 and started to focus more on my health. As I missed traditional Japanese food, I started cooking our family recipes here. My goal is to make people happy and healthy through my Japanese food! I hold a Certificate of Natural Food Coordinator. Follow me on Instagram @japanesecookingclass_goldcoast Facebook facebook.com/herocooking You can get the latest recipes, ideas and news. bottom of page

Accessibility Online Portal Contact us What's on News and updates Transform Mandurah Visit Mandurah Home Explore Mandurah Ocean Marina Marina services and facilities Marina services and facilities The Mandurah Ocean Marina is an aquatic playground offering glorious beaches, boardwalks, parks and piazzas. The marina provides a colourful mix of waterfront market stalls, shops, cafes and restaurants as well as modern facilities for both professional and recreational boating enthusiasts. Marina Administration Office Located at 19 Fathom Turn and open Monday to Friday 8am - 4pm, the Marina Administration Office can assist you with: Boat pen hire Sale of fenders and boating power cords Navigational Charts can be obtained from Department of Transport Website: https://www.transport.wa.gov.au/imarine/nautical-charts.asp Dolphin Quay Shopping Mall For a list of stalls and contact numbers visit the Dolphin Quay website . name: The Maylands Hotel
homepage_content: Maylands Hotel 0 The Maylands Hotel is a heritage neighbourhood pub offering all day dining BOOK A TABLE TAKE AWAY THE maylands hotel Nestled in the heart of the leafy Eastern Adelaide suburb of Maylands just 5 minutes from the Adelaide CBD, The Maylands Hotel Bar & Kitchen is a delightful century-old neighbourhood pub overlooking Cruickshank Reserve. A recognised landmark to the local community it offers a classic front bar, casual and intimate indoor spaces + a private function room. With a new lease on life following a tradition-defying refurbishment in 2021 and a prestigious award for Best Bistro Casual Dining (Inner Metropolitan) at the 2021 Australian Hotels Association (SA). Chilled vibes and good times for family and friends are guaranteed at this ‚Äòhome away from home‚Äô Adelaide establishment. There are definitely moments shared and moments made at The Maylands Hotel. OUR MENU BOOK A TABLE FUNCTIONS OPENING HOURS

name: Miss Perez Kitchen & Bar
homepage_content: Restaurant | Miss Perez Kitchen & Bar | Stirling top of page MISS PEREZ KITCHEN & BAR ABOUT US Miss Perez Kitchen & Bar is situated on one of the prettiest tree-lined street in Stirling. With its contemporary Australian cuisine, Miss Perez prides itself on sourcing local quailty ingredients. The menu draws on cuisines from Latin America, Spain and Australia. Alongside shared plates and more substantial options, there‚Äôs a range of burgers ‚Äì the most notable being the Perez Burger. To drink, there‚Äôs local VICE coffee, Adelaide Hills wine and local beers. Floor-to-ceiling windows grant stunning views of Stirling‚Äôs iconic oak trees, or you can sit beneath them on the outside deck. Larger groups can gather at the long tables inside, while two smaller rooms provide private nooks for smaller functions and gatherings. name: Meade Farm
homepage_content: Meade Farm | County Meath | Growers, Packers & Distributors of Fresh Food top of page MEADE FARM WELCOME TO GROWERS PACKERS DISTRIBUTORS SERVICE PROVIDERS our STORY The Meade Family, like all Irish farm families, has always spent a lot of their ‚Äòdown‚Äô time talking ‚Äòshop‚Äô or in this case, weather, harvest, etc. around the kitchen table. They debate about things like the best variety of spud, whether they should plant onion or carrots in a particular field. Thanks to their love of their family farm business, it has grown from being a small potato supplier to local shops to a grower, packer and distributor to retailers nationwide. ‚Äã Philip Sr. believes that bringing people good quality food to eat is as noble a vocation as there is. The next generation of Meades are following in his footsteps; they still believe that bringing premium quality, sustainable produce to consumers is a truly worthy enterprise. name: Catalina Restaurant
homepage_content: Home Page - Novotel √ó Our Partner Hotels: ibis Brisbane Airport | Pullman Brisbane Airport P: +61 7 3175 3100 Premium accommodation located conveniently within the Airport precinct Book Now Check-In Check-OUT Adults 1 2 3 children 0 1 2 3 Welcome To Novotel Brisbane Airport Hotel Location & Transport Novotel Brisbane Airport hotel is ideally located in Skygate, adjacent to DFO. The hotel is adjacent to the Gateway Arterial road and only minutes from the Domestic and International terminals. Novotel Brisbane Airport offers accommodation near Brisbane Entertainment Centre, Brisbane Racing Club, Brisbane Racing Carnival, Eagle Farm and Doomben Race courses and 20 minutes from the Brisbane CBD. The hotel also has a shuttle service at $8 per person which operates on a scheduled loop service between the hours of 3.55am to 9.15am and stops at the Domestic and International Terminals. For more information on pick-up locations and scheduled times click here . Novotel Brisbane Airport Hotel also offers undercover parking with an additional fee. Please contact the Reception team for pricing. Convenient and Quality Accommodation Spacious, contemporary in design and adaptable, Novotel Brisbane Airport accommodation is truly a place for living, perfect for all your needs. 360 Room View Standard King from $289 Sleeps 2 Wireless internet Air conditioned Tea & coffee making facilities Television Size: 26m2 View Room Book Room 360 Room View Executive Suite from $439 Sleeps up to 4 Wireless internet Air conditioned Tea & coffee making facilities Nespresso coffee machine Bath robes Complimentary newspaper Two Televisions Size: 52m2 View Room Book Room 360 Room View Catalina Bar & Restaurant Boasting contemporary interiors and a relaxed atmosphere, Catalina Bar and Restaurant offers a range of modern dining options throughout the day for your convenience and enjoyment.. Hickory Smoked Rump Steak $32 Hickory smoked rump steak 250g served with choice of fat chips or philly mash & confit cherry tomatoes. More Info Special Offers Day Stay & Refresh Day, Stay & Refresh Package. What a difference a day makes. Take a break between flights or maybe freshen up before your next meeting Find Out More Entertainment Package Seeing a show at Brisbane Entertainment Centre? Give yourself the celebrity treatment to compliment your existing tickets, Find Out More Racing Package Stay close to all the racing action on Saturday nights. Avoid the hassle of heading home and gallop straight to the hotel for a relaxing night's stay with our Racing Package. Find Out More MEETINGS & EVENTS Novotel Brisbane Airport offers a state of the art Brisbane conference venue ideal for meetings, conferences and events. Our attentive and experienced team of creative and flexible professionals will work with you to ensure optimal meeting success. Choose from six dedicated meeting and event rooms with capacity for up to 120 delegates theatre style, located ideally close to Brisbane Airport. Find out More Brisbane Airport Hotels "As always the staff perform at an extremely high level and should be congratulated. This is across-the-board from reception and concierge to restaurant and housekeeping. Rooms are very spacious, clean with a good-sized bathroom. Particular mention to lack of noise and excellent black-out curtains which aids a good night's sleep. Will be back. Oh, and 10 minutes from the airport." TrishMcQ - Dampier, Australia Brisbane Airport Hotels Group Close BOOK DIRECT Book direct with the hotel to avoid disappointment! With an unfortunate increase in fraudulent websites we recommend you contact the hotel directly to make your reservation. Contact our team today to secure your reservation safely - (07) 3175 3100

Welcome To The Old Sydney Hotel A Local Favourite In Maryborough Eat Drink Gaming A Family Friendly Dining Destination Just a short walk from Queen's Park and the Mary River, the Old Sydney Hotel sits in the heart of Maryborough. At its core, the Old Sydney Hotel offers a comfortable front bar and everything you‚Äôd expect from your local pub. We pride ourselves on delivering quality pub dining in a relaxed environment. Our menu showcases premium Queensland produce with modern seasonal dishes and quality pub classics. If it's a drink you're after, look no further than our Sports Bar. It‚Äôs the perfect place in Maryborough to sip a brew and relax in one of our lounges, with sport broadcasting across a number of large TV screens. Choose one of our beers on tap, or take a look at our spirits, cider and wine list. For those after a quick bite, we have a refined menu available with pub classics that are suited perfectly to enjoying with mates. View Menu Book Now WHAT'S ON Bistro Whether you‚Äôre stopping in for a family lunch, an overdue catch up with friends, an intimate date night or any other occasion, our spacious Bistro is the perfect place. We pride ourselves on delivering quality pub dining in a relaxed environment. Our menu showcases Australian produce with modern seasonal dishes and quality pub classics. We‚Äôre open seven days a week for lunch and for dinner, so book a table online or head in and speak with our team today. View Menu Book Now Sports Bar When the game is on, our Sports Bar is the best place to be. Enjoy comfortable lounge seating while watching on one of our large TV screens, with a selection of sports broadcasting live at all times. You won't miss a minute of the action with full access to our TAB facilities. We‚Äôll serve up some of your favourite pub classics to accompany the huge beverage selection we have, including an enormous range of ice cold beer on tap, not to mention our wine, cider and spirit lists. Welcome to The Phoenix Hotel A Favourite of Locals and Visitors in Gympie Eat Drink Functions Gaming Quality Food and Drinks with Country Hospitality The Phoenix Hotel was built in 1887, just 20 years after James Nash discovered gold in Gympie, and was named after the North Phoenix No. 2 Mine. To this day there are three tunnels under the Hotel, the closest being 100 metres from the surface. These days the Phoenix Hotel is a warm, friendly and tastefully refurbished dining and entertainment venue situated in the heart of the local community of Gympie. We specialise in quality pub dining with country hospitality. The Phoenix is a ‚Äòmust do‚Äô when in the beautiful town of Gympie. Situated on a hilltop looking over the valley, it‚Äôs the perfect spot for a cold drink and hearty meal or to stay a while and let the world go by. We have kids and seniors menus, as well as weekly specials to ensure great value dining for the whole family. With seating for 140 people in air conditioned comfort, you‚Äôll be dining in bliss with us at the Phoenix Hotel Bistro. Make a booking online or come in today to see our friendly staff. View Menu Book Now No. 2 Lounge Bar Named after the North Phoenix No. 2 mine, our beautifully furnished No. 2 Lounge Bar is the perfect destination for drinks on any occasion. Specialising in boutique beers and simply made cocktails, our range of drinks is suitable and perfect to match any palette. You can deter¬≠mine the cur¬≠rent fire dan¬≠ger rat¬≠ing by check¬≠ing the Fire Ban Dis¬≠trict map on the CFS website. Out¬≠side of the park Please con¬≠tact a local wildlife res¬≠cue group Marine mam¬≠mals If you find a sick or strand¬≠ed marine mam¬≠mal (includ¬≠ing whales, seals, sea lions and dol¬≠phins), please con¬≠tact Vic¬≠tor Har¬≠bor Nation¬≠al Parks and Wildlife Ser¬≠vice Office on (+61) 8336 0901 or the after-hours duty offi¬≠cer on 0427 556 676 (out¬≠side of busi¬≠ness hours) When to visit June to Octo¬≠ber is the per¬≠fect time to vis¬≠it for whale watch¬≠ing activ¬≠i¬≠ties. Getting there Gran¬≠ite Island Recre¬≠ation Park is locat¬≠ed off the coast of Vic¬≠tor Har¬≠bor, approx¬≠i¬≠mate¬≠ly 100km south of Adelaide. Granite Island Recreation Park Caf√© The Gran¬≠ite Island Recre¬≠ation Park caf√© is open dai¬≠ly from 9:00am ‚Äì 5:00pm. For fur¬≠ther infor¬≠ma¬≠tion phone (08) 8429 9656. Little penguins The Lit¬≠tle Penguin (Also known as fairy pen¬≠guin, blue pen¬≠guin or lit¬≠tle blue penguin) The Lit¬≠tle Pen¬≠guin is the world‚Äôs small¬≠est pen¬≠guin species and is well known to most vis¬≠i¬≠tors to Australia‚Äôs south¬≠ern coast¬≠line. It stands about 35 cm tall and weighs about 1.2kg. By com¬≠par¬≠i¬≠son the Emper¬≠or Pen¬≠guin, which is the largest pen¬≠guin in the world, stands over 110 cm and can weigh 30kg. The Lit¬≠tle Pen¬≠guin is found only in Aus¬≠tralia and New Zealand and is the only pen¬≠guin to breed in Aus¬≠tralia. Large num¬≠bers can occur where suit¬≠able con¬≠di¬≠tions are present. Lit¬≠tle pen¬≠guins favour rocky shore¬≠lines, just like Gran¬≠ite Island, which pro¬≠vide suit¬≠able breed¬≠ing sites. The num¬≠ber of Lit¬≠tle Pen¬≠guins on Gran¬≠ite Island has declined from 1600 pen¬≠guins in 2001 to 20 adult pen¬≠guins count¬≠ed in the last cen¬≠sus in Octo¬≠ber 2021. Despite, the low num¬≠ber the colony has increased from 16 pen¬≠guins in 2020. The active bur¬≠rows on the island are mon¬≠i¬≠tored with the use of remote cameras. The defin¬≠i¬≠tive cause of this decline is still unclear, although a 2007 PIR¬≠SA study iden¬≠ti¬≠fied a num¬≠ber of fac¬≠tors includ¬≠ing: changes in the marine envi¬≠ron¬≠ment, pre¬≠da¬≠tion pres¬≠sure, and rat pre¬≠da¬≠tion on chicks. Study is ongo¬≠ing on the island and a rat bait¬≠ing pro¬≠gram and mea¬≠sures to pre¬≠vent fox¬≠es access¬≠ing the island are cur¬≠rent¬≠ly in place to pro¬≠tect the eggs and young chicks from predation. Lit¬≠tle Pen¬≠guins lay 2 eggs per clutch and incu¬≠bate them for approx¬≠i¬≠mate¬≠ly 36 days. Chicks fledge when they are typ¬≠i¬≠cal¬≠ly 59 days post hatch¬≠ing. Chicks are guard¬≠ed by at least one adult for around 3 weeks fol¬≠low¬≠ing hatch¬≠ing, alter¬≠nat¬≠ing for¬≠ag¬≠ing between the two adult birds. After 3 weeks both par¬≠ents leave the chicks to for¬≠age for food. For fur¬≠ther inter¬≠est¬≠ing infor¬≠ma¬≠tion please see our Lit¬≠tle pen¬≠guins fact sheet Lit¬≠tle Pen¬≠guins for¬≠age for food dur¬≠ing the day and will return to their bur¬≠rows dur¬≠ing the ear¬≠ly morn¬≠ing and late evening. Lit¬≠tle Pen¬≠guins are high¬≠ly sen¬≠si¬≠tive to dis¬≠tur¬≠bances from peo¬≠ple and ani¬≠mals, this can cause them to aban¬≠don their breed¬≠ing activ¬≠i¬≠ties and bur¬≠rows and impact their sur¬≠vival. Please adhere to the fol¬≠low¬≠ing guide¬≠lines to pro¬≠tect this vul¬≠ner¬≠a¬≠ble population: Keep your dis¬≠tance ‚Äî Do not approach a pen¬≠guin by less than 5 meters. The pen¬≠guins always have the‚Äã‚Äòright of way‚Äô. They are usu¬≠al¬≠ly return¬≠ing to their bur¬≠row or chicks. Don‚Äôt get between chicks and adult pen¬≠guins or obstruct a pen¬≠guin from get¬≠ting to its burrow. Turn the flash set¬≠ting off on your cam¬≠era. A cam¬≠era flash will blind a pen¬≠guin for up to three days mak¬≠ing them vul¬≠ner¬≠a¬≠ble to predation. Do not use a torch unless it has been fit¬≠ted with a red filter. Pen¬≠guins are high¬≠ly sen¬≠si¬≠tive to noise ‚Äì keep your noise lev¬≠el to a min¬≠i¬≠mum if you are near a pen¬≠guin or its burrow. Dogs are not per¬≠mit¬≠ted on the island and fines apply. Even the smell of dogs with¬≠in the colony will dis¬≠turb pen¬≠guins and may stop them from breeding. Moult¬≠ing pen¬≠guins may be easy to see in their bur¬≠rows but they are most vul¬≠ner¬≠a¬≠ble at this time. Their new feath¬≠ers are not yet water¬≠proof so they can¬≠not leave the bur¬≠row if disturbed. Pests and diseases Phy¬≠toph¬≠tho¬≠ra (fy-TOFF-tho¬≠ra), oth¬≠er¬≠wise known as root-rot fun¬≠gus, is killing our native plants and threat¬≠ens the sur¬≠vival of ani¬≠mals depend¬≠ing on plants for food and shelter. Phy¬≠toph¬≠tho¬≠ra brochure Traditional owners Abo¬≠rig¬≠i¬≠nal peo¬≠ples have occu¬≠pied, enjoyed and man¬≠aged the lands and waters of this State for thou¬≠sands of gen¬≠er¬≠a¬≠tions. For Abo¬≠rig¬≠i¬≠nal first nations, cre¬≠ation ances¬≠tors laid down the laws of the Coun¬≠try and bestowed a range of cus¬≠tom¬≠ary rights and oblig¬≠a¬≠tions to the many Abo¬≠rig¬≠i¬≠nal Nations across our state. At some of these places Abo¬≠rig¬≠i¬≠nal cul¬≠tur¬≠al pro¬≠to¬≠cols, such as restrict¬≠ed access, are pro¬≠mot¬≠ed and vis¬≠i¬≠tors are asked to respect the wish¬≠es of Tra¬≠di¬≠tion¬≠al Owners. It has sur¬≠vived the force of the ocean while the land sur¬≠round¬≠ing it has erod¬≠ed away. Bush¬≠walk¬≠ing safety Park maps Grade 1 ‚Äî No bush¬≠walk¬≠ing expe¬≠ri¬≠ence required, suit¬≠able for wheel¬≠chair users who have some¬≠one to assist them Vic¬≠tor Har¬≠bor to Gran¬≠ite Island Cause¬≠way (20 mins one-way, 650 metres) Nav¬≠i¬≠gate this trail on Google Street View Take a short stroll or horse tram ride over the wood¬≠en cause¬≠way that con¬≠nects the main¬≠land at Vic¬≠tor Har¬≠bor to Gran¬≠ite Island Recre¬≠ation Park. Grade 3 ‚Äî Suit¬≠able for most ages and fit¬≠ness levels Kai¬≠ki Walk (1 hour, 2.9km loop) Nav¬≠i¬≠gate this trail on Google Street View The trail is a great way for peo¬≠ple, includ¬≠ing fam¬≠i¬≠lies with chil¬≠dren and strollers, to dis¬≠cov¬≠er the island. Granite Island Recreation Park Caf√© The Gran¬≠ite Island Recre¬≠ation Park caf√© is open dai¬≠ly from 9:00am ‚Äì 5:00pm. For fur¬≠ther infor¬≠ma¬≠tion phone (08) 8429 9656. Seat¬≠ing is avail¬≠able with¬≠in the caf√© with a range of local¬≠ly sourced pas¬≠tries, sand¬≠wich¬≠es and snacks on offer. On a warm day the grass area in front of the caf√© is per¬≠fect for kids, with dol¬≠phins and sea lions often mak¬≠ing an appear¬≠ance in the distance. Whale watching Take your binoc¬≠u¬≠lars, cast your eyes out to sea and you may be lucky enough to spot a south¬≠ern right whale between May and October. The south¬≠ern right whales‚Äô unique affin¬≠i¬≠ty for coastal inshore waters makes them the per¬≠fect species for land-based whale watch¬≠ing, you can eas¬≠i¬≠ly spend many hours view¬≠ing their play¬≠ful antics. Some¬≠times the whales approach as close as 100m from shore, pro¬≠vid¬≠ing a bird‚Äôs eye view of their immense size and rotund, 18m body. The most com¬≠mon are the south¬≠ern right whale, hump¬≠back whale, sperm whale, blue whale and orca whale (killer whale). Of these you are most like¬≠ly to spot a south¬≠ern right whale along the South Aus¬≠tralian coast. Little penguins The Lit¬≠tle Penguin (Also known as fairy pen¬≠guin, blue pen¬≠guin or lit¬≠tle blue penguin) The Lit¬≠tle Pen¬≠guin is the world‚Äôs small¬≠est pen¬≠guin species and is well known to most vis¬≠i¬≠tors to Australia‚Äôs south¬≠ern coast¬≠line. It stands about 35 cm tall and weighs about 1.2kg. By com¬≠par¬≠i¬≠son the Emper¬≠or Pen¬≠guin, which is the largest pen¬≠guin in the world, stands over 110 cm and can weigh 30kg. The Lit¬≠tle Pen¬≠guin is found only in Aus¬≠tralia and New Zealand and is the only pen¬≠guin to breed in Aus¬≠tralia. Large num¬≠bers can occur where suit¬≠able con¬≠di¬≠tions are present. Lit¬≠tle pen¬≠guins favour rocky shore¬≠lines, just like Gran¬≠ite Island, which pro¬≠vide suit¬≠able breed¬≠ing sites. The avail¬≠abil¬≠i¬≠ty of feed¬≠ing grounds also deter¬≠mines the size and suc¬≠cess of a colony. The num¬≠ber of Lit¬≠tle Pen¬≠guins on Gran¬≠ite Island has declined from 1600 pen¬≠guins in 2001 to 20 adult pen¬≠guins count¬≠ed in the last cen¬≠sus in Octo¬≠ber 2021. Despite, the low num¬≠ber the colony has increased from 16 pen¬≠guins in 2020. The active bur¬≠rows on the island are mon¬≠i¬≠tored with the use of remote cameras. The defin¬≠i¬≠tive cause of this decline is still unclear, although a 2007 PIR¬≠SA study iden¬≠ti¬≠fied a num¬≠ber of fac¬≠tors includ¬≠ing: changes in the marine envi¬≠ron¬≠ment, pre¬≠da¬≠tion pres¬≠sure, and rat pre¬≠da¬≠tion on chicks. Study is ongo¬≠ing on the island and a rat bait¬≠ing pro¬≠gram and mea¬≠sures to pre¬≠vent fox¬≠es access¬≠ing the island are cur¬≠rent¬≠ly in place to pro¬≠tect the eggs and young chicks from predation. Lit¬≠tle Pen¬≠guins lay 2 eggs per clutch and incu¬≠bate them for approx¬≠i¬≠mate¬≠ly 36 days. Chicks fledge when they are typ¬≠i¬≠cal¬≠ly 59 days post hatch¬≠ing. Chicks are guard¬≠ed by at least one adult for around 3 weeks fol¬≠low¬≠ing hatch¬≠ing, alter¬≠nat¬≠ing for¬≠ag¬≠ing between the two adult birds. After 3 weeks both par¬≠ents leave the chicks to for¬≠age for food. For fur¬≠ther inter¬≠est¬≠ing infor¬≠ma¬≠tion please see our Lit¬≠tle pen¬≠guins fact sheet Lit¬≠tle Pen¬≠guins for¬≠age for food dur¬≠ing the day and will return to their bur¬≠rows dur¬≠ing the ear¬≠ly morn¬≠ing and late evening. Lit¬≠tle Pen¬≠guins are high¬≠ly sen¬≠si¬≠tive to dis¬≠tur¬≠bances from peo¬≠ple and ani¬≠mals, this can cause them to aban¬≠don their breed¬≠ing activ¬≠i¬≠ties and bur¬≠rows and impact their sur¬≠vival. Please adhere to the fol¬≠low¬≠ing guide¬≠lines to pro¬≠tect this vul¬≠ner¬≠a¬≠ble population: Keep your dis¬≠tance ‚Äî Do not approach a pen¬≠guin by less than 5 meters. The pen¬≠guins always have the‚Äã‚Äòright of way‚Äô. They are usu¬≠al¬≠ly return¬≠ing to their bur¬≠row or chicks. Don‚Äôt get between chicks and adult pen¬≠guins or obstruct a pen¬≠guin from get¬≠ting to its burrow. Turn the flash set¬≠ting off on your cam¬≠era. A cam¬≠era flash will blind a pen¬≠guin for up to three days mak¬≠ing them vul¬≠ner¬≠a¬≠ble to predation. Do not use a torch unless it has been fit¬≠ted with a red filter. Pen¬≠guins are high¬≠ly sen¬≠si¬≠tive to noise ‚Äì keep your noise lev¬≠el to a min¬≠i¬≠mum if you are near a pen¬≠guin or its burrow. Dogs are not per¬≠mit¬≠ted on the island and fines apply. name: Royal Garden Wagga
homepage_content: Get proof of COVID-19 vaccination | NSW Government Get proof of COVID-19 vaccination There are options for providing proof of your COVID-19 vaccinations, depending on your situation. Last updated: 08 April 2024 Listen On this page COVID-19 digital certificate changes On 2 December 2023, the COVID-19 digital certificate was replaced by the COVID-19 and Influenza Immunisation History Statement. Find out more about how to access your immunisation history statement on the Services Australia website . Methods of proving your COVID-19 vaccinations There are options available to show proof of your vaccinations: An immunisation history statement can be printed, stored securely in your Express Plus Medicare app, or downloaded to your mobile phone digital wallet. The immunisation history lists your COVID-19 vaccinations and influenza vaccinations. More information is available on the Services Australia website . How to access proof of your COVID-19 vaccination Your immunisation history statement can display all the COVID-19 vaccine doses you‚Äôve had. If you are eligible for Medicare You can download your immunisation history statement using: your Medicare online account through myGov the Express Plus Medicare mobile app your My Health Record . If you are not eligible for Medicare You will need an Individual Healthcare Identifier (IHI) to register your vaccinations online if you are not eligible for Medicare. If you don't already have an IHI, you can apply for one and link it using the Individual Healthcare Identifiers service (IHI service) through myGov. To do this, sign in to myGov then: Select Services or Link your first service . Select Individual Healthcare Identifiers service and then follow the prompts. For more information, visit the Services Australia website . If you were vaccinated overseas If you‚Äôve received an approved vaccine while overseas, you can have it recorded on the Australian Immunisation Register (AIR). It will then appear on your immunisation history statement. Recognised vaccination providers in Australia can help you add approved overseas vaccinations to the AIR. Find out how to add your overseas COVID-19 vaccinations to the AIR . Carry proof of your COVID-19 vaccination Your digital wallet You can add your immunisation history statement to a digital wallet . A digital wallet is an app on your mobile device that also stores information such as debit cards, tickets and boarding passes. The Medicare app Your immunisation history statement can be stored securely in your Express Plus Medicare app. Printing a paper history You can print your immunisation history statement to carry with you as proof of your vaccination status. You can print a copy by downloading a PDF using your Medicare online account through myGov or the Express Plus Medicare app. If you can‚Äôt access proof of your COVID-19 vaccination online, you can: ask your vaccination provider ‚Äì such as your doctor ‚Äì to print your immunisation history statement for you call the Australian Immunisation Register on 1800 653 809 between 8am and 5pm, Monday to Friday. Ask them to send your immunisation history statement to you by mail. If you need an interpreter, please call the Telephone Interpreter Service (TIS) on 131 450 . If your COVID-19 vaccination information is incorrect you need to ask your vaccination provider to update the Australian Immunisation Register. For more information on updating your immunisation history statement . Proving a medical exemption If you‚Äôre unable to be vaccinated for COVID-19 because it may be harmful to you (known as a medical contraindication), you can get proof of your exemption. First, your doctor will need to update your record on the Australian Immunisation Register to say you have a medical contraindication. You can show proof of your medical contraindication with: a downloaded or printed copy of your immunisation history statement, or a NSW Health medical contraindication form completed by a registered medical practitioner (only valid in NSW). homepage_content: Get proof of COVID-19 vaccination | NSW Government Get proof of COVID-19 vaccination There are options for providing proof of your COVID-19 vaccinations, depending on your situation. Last updated: 08 April 2024 Listen On this page COVID-19 digital certificate changes On 2 December 2023, the COVID-19 digital certificate was replaced by the COVID-19 and Influenza Immunisation History Statement. Find out more about how to access your immunisation history statement on the Services Australia website . Methods of proving your COVID-19 vaccinations There are options available to show proof of your vaccinations: An immunisation history statement can be printed, stored securely in your Express Plus Medicare app, or downloaded to your mobile phone digital wallet. The immunisation history lists your COVID-19 vaccinations and influenza vaccinations. More information is available on the Services Australia website . How to access proof of your COVID-19 vaccination Your immunisation history statement can display all the COVID-19 vaccine doses you‚Äôve had. If you are eligible for Medicare You can download your immunisation history statement using: your Medicare online account through myGov the Express Plus Medicare mobile app your My Health Record . If you are not eligible for Medicare You will need an Individual Healthcare Identifier (IHI) to register your vaccinations online if you are not eligible for Medicare. If you don't already have an IHI, you can apply for one and link it using the Individual Healthcare Identifiers service (IHI service) through myGov. To do this, sign in to myGov then: Select Services or Link your first service . Select Individual Healthcare Identifiers service and then follow the prompts. For more information, visit the Services Australia website . If you were vaccinated overseas If you‚Äôve received an approved vaccine while overseas, you can have it recorded on the Australian Immunisation Register (AIR). It will then appear on your immunisation history statement. Recognised vaccination providers in Australia can help you add approved overseas vaccinations to the AIR. Find out how to add your overseas COVID-19 vaccinations to the AIR . Carry proof of your COVID-19 vaccination Your digital wallet You can add your immunisation history statement to a digital wallet . A digital wallet is an app on your mobile device that also stores information such as debit cards, tickets and boarding passes. The Medicare app Your immunisation history statement can be stored securely in your Express Plus Medicare app. Printing a paper history You can print your immunisation history statement to carry with you as proof of your vaccination status. You can print a copy by downloading a PDF using your Medicare online account through myGov or the Express Plus Medicare app. If you can‚Äôt access proof of your COVID-19 vaccination online, you can: ask your vaccination provider ‚Äì such as your doctor ‚Äì to print your immunisation history statement for you call the Australian Immunisation Register on 1800 653 809 between 8am and 5pm, Monday to Friday. Ask them to send your immunisation history statement to you by mail. If you need an interpreter, please call the Telephone Interpreter Service (TIS) on 131 450 . If your COVID-19 vaccination information is incorrect you need to ask your vaccination provider to update the Australian Immunisation Register. For more information on updating your immunisation history statement . Proving a medical exemption If you‚Äôre unable to be vaccinated for COVID-19 because it may be harmful to you (known as a medical contraindication), you can get proof of your exemption. First, your doctor will need to update your record on the Australian Immunisation Register to say you have a medical contraindication. You can show proof of your medical contraindication with: a downloaded or printed copy of your immunisation history statement, or a NSW Health medical contraindication form completed by a registered medical practitioner (only valid in NSW). Related information MyGov Medicare, health cover and MyHealth record Frequently asked questions: COVID-19 vaccines (National Centre for Immunisation Research and Surveillance) download Download as PDF print Print this page share Share this page Facebook LinkedIn X Email mail Top of page north

As you plan where to eat during your stay in Adelaide, you can discover an exceptional dining experience without ever leaving the hotel. ADELAIDE ROCKFORD DINING OPTIONS Start your morning with a delicious serviced breakfast. And if you're short on time, why not grab a takeaway coffee from the Rockford Lounge? The Deck is the perfect meeting place for a pre-dinner beverage or a relaxing dining experience from 5.30pm Our Rockford Bar & Deck is open from 4:30pm Mon - Sat, with some great Australian classic dishes on offer you will be spoilt for choice. Also, be sure to join us every evening from 4.30pm - 6pm for happy hour drinks. Breakfast: Mon - Fri 7.00AM - 10.00AM Sat & Sun 7.30AM - 10.30AM Public Holidays 7.30AM - 10.30AM In-Room Dining Available: 4:30PM - 9PM Monday to Saturday Dial 819 from your room or call (08) 8211 8255 from your mobile phone to be directed to the restaurant. Rockford Bar & Deck Mon - Sat 4.30PM - 9:00PM Rockford Restaurant Mon - Sat 5.30PM - 9:00PM Unless otherwise stated our Food and Beverage outlets will be closed on public holidays. Please note that the Rockford Restaurant and Bar as well as In-Room Dining will be closed from the 24th to the 26th of December for Christmas and 1st of December for New Years Day. name: Little Beach Reserve
homepage_content: Little Beach Reserve | Port Stephens Council This site uses cookies to analyse traffic, remember your preferences, and optimise your experience. Learn more. Accept Decline √ó Share this page Little Beach Reserve Listen Little Beach is a small beach facing north west adjacent to the Halifax Holiday Park and the Nelson Head lighthouse reserve. The Little Beach foreshore has both a grassed area and beach area ideal for family and social club gatherings. The beach is ideal for young children with its sandy expanse and gentle waters. This site is very popular with both a public jetty and boat launching ramp. There is a fish cleaning table for successful anglers and is popular with pelicans. Little Beach features a disabled access jetty. The ramp allows wheel chair direct access into the ocean. Facilities Public amenities including disabled toilets Barbeque & picnic facilities Play equipment including disabled play area Boat ramp Fish cleaning tables Car park and trailer parking Wharf with disabled access √ó Close

homepage_content: Little Beach Reserve | Port Stephens Council This site uses cookies to analyse traffic, remember your preferences, and optimise your experience. Learn more. Accept Decline √ó Share this page Little Beach Reserve Listen Little Beach is a small beach facing north west adjacent to the Halifax Holiday Park and the Nelson Head lighthouse reserve. The Little Beach foreshore has both a grassed area and beach area ideal for family and social club gatherings. The beach is ideal for young children with its sandy expanse and gentle waters. This site is very popular with both a public jetty and boat launching ramp. There is a fish cleaning table for successful anglers and is popular with pelicans. Little Beach features a disabled access jetty. The ramp allows wheel chair direct access into the ocean. name: Solander Dining and Bar
homepage_content: Solander Dining & Bar | Sophisticated All-Day Dining in Sydney book now terms and conditions By providing your information and participating in this promotion, you acknowledge and agree to our Privacy Statement . You also acknowledge and agree that the personal information you provide will be used for the purposes detailed in our Privacy Statement. This may include: providing services and transactions, better understanding customer needs, and sending special offers, promotions, surveys and other marketing information by email, post or telesales. In addition, you acknowledge that your information will be entered into our database controlled by Hilton at its headquarters in the U.S. You further agree that all Hilton companies, owners and operators of our franchised and managed hotels, and service providers, may receive and use this data for any of the purposes listed above and access it globally, including from countries where data protection laws may differ from those of your home country. For your security, the data protections provisions of the Privacy Statement shall apply to all data processing, and you may request rights of access, correction, and objection as described therein. If you do not wish to receive marketing information from Hilton you may Unsubscribe at any time. Close Eat When naturalist Daniel Solander arrived in Australia he extensively explored and researched the region‚Äôs flora and fauna. Like him, we have explored the region‚Äôs best available produce and have partnered with a number of local suppliers in order to provide the best seasonal and sustainable meals from farm to table. Operating Hours: Breakfast- Mon to Fri: 6:30am to 10:00am; Sat to Sun: 7:00am to 10:30am Lunch- Mon to Sat: 12:00pm to 3:00pm Dinner- Mon to Sat: 5:00pm to 10:00pm Lunch Menu Dinner Menu Set Menu (for groups 10 or more) Bottomless Rose Menu Drink Start your morning with a cup of barista made Will & Co coffee. As night falls, settle at our emerald green terrazzo marble bar and make your selections from our botanical-inspired cocktails, mocktails, boutique Australian and international spirits, wines and craft beers. Events With our flexible bar and restaurant spaces that extend onto our lush atrium, we can create intimate spaces, or cater to groups of up to 140 people. A minimum spend is required for area or full venue bookings. Call +61 2 8297 6500 or email to plan your event. Festive Packages About Naturalist Daniel Solander (1733-1782), was integral to the early documentation and collection of Australian plants. Today, we tip our hat to this whimsical character in our botanical-inspired restaurant and bar. A modern Australian all-day dining experience Michael Vane, Man of Many Gallery Find Us Solander Dining & Bar 65 Sussex Street Sydney NSW 2000 Solander Dining & Bar 65 Sussex Street Sydney NSW 2000 Telephone: +61 2 8297 6500 Email: solander_enquiries@hilton.com Hours: Breakfast 6:30am to 10:30am Monday to Friday 7:00am to 10:30am Saturday and Sunday Lunch 12:00pm to 3:00pm Monday to Friday Dinner/ Bar 5:00pm until late Monday to Saturday Closed on Sunday A boutique hotel and modern classic, moments from Barangaroo on the Western Corridor. With professional service, students manage every aspect to showcase their skills in menu planning, food preparation, budgeting and restaurant operations. Sourcing wines from overseas added another dimension to our wine-tasting experience and was in contrast to our usual local wines. Every course offered something different, surprising and enjoyable and initiated lots of discussion around the tables. ‚Äî Anonymous Our members love the Epicure concept and, as parents, grandparents, aunts and uncles, love seeing students learning skills that will set them up for an enjoyable and successful career in the hospitality industry. We also loved hearing from the students and learning a little bit about each one. ‚Äî Anonymous "The food is always wonderful, but our recent visit was particularly excellent. The young chefs truly deserve top marks for their outstanding work!" ‚Äî Gloria Rogerson "What a great time we had last night! Please pass on our compliments to everyone involved that the meal was delicious and the evening truly delightful. A special thank you to Chloe, who looked after us with such care and attention. And of course, our thanks extend to the entire team, including the hard-working supervisors. We had a wonderful evening!" ‚Äî Jennifer Whawell "Thank you so much for dinner last night, the food was amazing! The waitstaff, though a little nervous, were incredibly polite and clearly engaged in the learning experience. I wish everyone great success in their course and can‚Äôt wait to see what your next menu has to offer." ‚Äî Neeshia Delaporte "I just wanted to say a huge thank you to all the Hospitality and Commercial cookery teams that were involved in running the service last night (20th August). All of the wait staff that assisted our table were very professional and responded quickly to all requests. The food was absolutely delicious and presented beautifully. Everyone expressed what a great night they had and how much they enjoyed the meal. The birthday girl was very appreciative of the rendition of Happy Birthday provided by the teams when the cake was delivered, this made the celebration special. Millie was our main waitperson and showed professionalism and confidence, we cannot fault her service. All the students and staff were friendly and welcoming." ‚Äî Toni Griffiths ‚ÄòThe service and menu on our evening dining at the Epicure southwest was impressive! It's great to see young people putting their training into practical service and we couldn't fault anything, great work! Look forward to dining there again.‚Äù ‚Äî Anonymous chat apply top

The Front bar is an ideal place to play a few games of pool or place a few bets on the TAB or Keno. POPULAR AMONGST THE LOCALS, THE FAMILY FRIENDLY BISTRO IS SPACIOUS WITH A CLASSIC AUSSIE SELF-SERVE SALAD BAR AND AN ENCLOSED INDOOR PLAY AREA FOR THE KIDS. IN THE WARMER MONTHS GUESTS TAKE TO THE ALFRESCO BEER GARDEN. The South Eastern Hotel is a great place to hold your special function, meeting, birthday, corporate event or any other occasion. NO MATTER THE OCCASION, WE GO ABOVE AND BEYOND IN ASSISTING YOU WITH THIS GOAL. OUR MENU BOOK A TABLE FUNCTIONS OPENING HOURS

WELCOME TO THE SPRINGWOOD HOTEL A LOCAL FAVOURITE Eat Drink Functions Stay IN THE HEART OF SPRINGWOOD A pillar in the community, Springwood Hotel we're connected to our customers and beyond. Right next to the Springwood Shopping Mall, Springwood Hotel has all anyone could need in their local. A place to bring your family to share a meal in our kid-friendly bistro, a place to catch up with your mates over a beer at the Barra Bar or a place for a night out to catch some live tunes. Book Now WHAT'S ON FEAST Feast is designed to celebrate the good times and everyday pleasures in life. Relax with your family and friends and have your pick from our delicious selection. Our buffet is better than ever, offering hot soups and entrees, fresh salads, succulent roasts with all the trimmings, chicken parmas, sliders, an extensive range of Asian dishes and more. We now serve seafood every day of the week, including whole prawns, salmon and mussels. To finish it off, you‚Äôll be spoiled for choice with our wide range of dessert options. Whether it‚Äôs an overdue family catch up or a weekly dinner, Feast is the perfect place to share the moments. We‚Äôre all about celebration, sharing, choice and variety - there truly is something for everyone. We‚Äôre open every day for lunch and dinner, so make a booking online today! Our digital payments service speeds up your arrival time so you can head straight into the buffet. You can also order drinks on your phone while you're sitting at your table and we'll deliver them to you! ADULTS: $37.00 SENIORS: $23.00 CHILDREN (4-12 years): $16.00 KIDS (3 years and under): FREE Book Now THE BARRA BAR Your local pub with the atmosphere to match. Come and have a drink with your mates in our Barra Bar. We have a pool table that sure to settle any bet you have with your mates, we serve your pub favourites here, best enjoyed while the games on. ACCOMMODATION by nightcap hotels Being centrally located, The Springwood Hotel is the perfect place between Brisbane and the Gold Coast. Situated in Logan city‚Äôs commercial business district, our hotel is located only 15 minutes from Brisbane‚Äôs CBD, 30 minutes from The Gold Coast CBD and only 20 minutes from Brisbane‚Äôs airport. Our single style hotel rooms are newly renovated, and each include tea and coffee facilities, a bar fridge, television and air conditioning. While you‚Äôre staying, dine in at our Feast Buffet, or order a meal from our Barra Bar. We are a Nightcap Hotels location. You can view full room details and book via the links below. Book a room Learn More FUNCTIONS If you're looking for a place to celebrate, we've got you covered. Whether it be for an intimate dinner, a conference meeting, an outdoor cocktail occasion, or even an end of year office party, we've got everything and more. We have two function rooms that can be transformed into what you're after, A large room suitable to cater up to 160 people cocktail style, and a laid back yet stylish alfresco area with your own private bar. homepage_content: Best Burger Restaurant in Melbourne - Simpsons Burgers Skip to content Menu Order Now Facebook Instagram Menu Simpsons Burgers Indulge in the Irresistible Taste of Australia's Finest Burgers. At Simpsons Burgers, we craft more than just burgers; we create experiences. Nestled in the heart of Australia, our passion for flavour and quality shines through in every bite. From juicy patties to handpicked fresh ingredients, each element is thoughtfully curated to deliver an unforgettable dining adventure. See Menu Order Now About Us Welcome to Simpsons Burgers, your cozy Melbourne hideaway that began its flavorful journey a decade ago. Sturt School for Wood MSF40222 Certificate IV in Furniture Design and Manufacturing Sturt School for Wood‚Äôs renowned year-long intensive course is guided by the world‚Äôs finest master furniture makers. Nowhere in Australia can you learn from as many furniture experts of this calibre. Sturt graduates are in demand in industry and honed to become the furniture makers and designers of the future. Learn more A History of Sturt Founded in 1941 Sturt was founded in 1941 by Winifred West (1881‚Äì1971) when she retired as headmistress of Frensham, the independent secondary school for girls which she had established in 1913. Miss West's intent was to provide further education in crafts, music and drama for children who had left Mittagong Primary School, and for adults seeking useful and creative skills. Learn more Frensham Schools Classes Design and Fabrication Studios Sturt plays an essential role in a Frensham Schools education. The Design and Fabrication Studios, formerly a weaving studio and a caf√©, refurbished into a contemporary learning space in 2015 to form a creative hub where expert teachers lead courses in digital design and fabrication, supported by the latest technologies. Welcome To The Sunnybank Hotel The Home of Live Sport Eat Drink Functions Stay Gaming A Relaxed Atmosphere to Meet With Family and Friends Sitting on McCullough Street, Sunnybank Hotel sits in the very heart of Sunnybank located in Brisbane's south. A 15 minute drive from Southbank and Brisbane CBD, and only one hour from the golden beaches of the Gold Coast, we‚Äôve been serving locals and visitors for many years on Brisbane‚Äôs Southside. In our Live Bar Bistro, the focus is on food and live sport on one of our three massive HD projectors. You can expect delicious meals, sourcing fresh local produce from suppliers we've built solid relationships with. We place significant importance on ensuring our ingredients are fresh, to bring you succulent steaks, fresh seafood, healthy salads and wholesome pastas plus all the classic pub fare you know and love; all made with passion and care from the dedicated chefs in our kitchen. If you're after a drink, stop in to our Sports Bar, within close proximity to the old QE2 Stadium which was a staple amongst Queenslanders. Playing host to the 1982 Commonwealth Games in Brisbane, along with Broncos home games for years and, of course, AC/DC. Choose an ice cold beer on tap, or decide between our wine, spirit and cocktail varieties. You‚Äôll find yourself in the perfect spot to catch the game on one of our huge screens - all whilst enjoying great food and good company. Whether you're catching up with mates, settling in for an overdue family lunch or celebrating a milestone, the Sunnybank Hotel is the perfect place to meet. View Menu Book Now WHAT'S ON Live Bar Bistro In the Live Bar Bistro, our focus is on delicious food and live sport. You can expect delicious meals highlighting fresh local produce brought to you by suppliers we've built solid relationships with. Built to seat 130 people, we have a selection of delicious, succulent steaks, fresh seafood, wholesome pastas and all the pub favourites you know love with a modern twist. It is the perfect place for an intimate date night, a family catch up or dinner with friends. We place a significant importance on ensuring our ingredients are fresh, with 100% Australian Graziers beef which is never frozen, 100% Australian chicken, hormone and antibiotic free, and 100% Australian seafood from sustainable fish stocks. You can be sure that when dining with us you're supporting local Australian producers, and dining on delicious meals made with passion and care from the dedicated chefs in our kitchen. We are open for lunch every day from 11:30 am, so book a table online or head in and speak to our friendly team. View Menu Book Now Sports Bar Our Sports Bar is within close proximity to the old QE2 Stadium which was a staple amongst Queenslanders. Playing host to the 1982 Commonwealth Games in Brisbane, along with Broncos home games for years and of course, AC/DC. We've been the go-to to catch the latest game or a sporting achievement for decades, and there's nothing we love more than seeing the reaction from our guests when their team is doing well. Our bar has a huge selection of ice cold beer available on tap for you to choose from, not to mention a huge list of wine, cider, spirits and cocktails. We have numerous viewing options to catch the latest game and a variety of sound zones so you get the full viewing experience. Functions The Sunnybank Hotel is available for your next function, be it a birthday, corporate lunch, Christmas party or family celebration. No matter what the occasion, we will ensure your event is planned and executed exactly how you'd like. We offer a delicious range of cocktail platters to enhance your event, and can tailor our space, furniture arrangement and food offering based on your needs. Our function events manager is here to help you with your function requirements. Get in touch with our team now, and start planning the event you've always wanted. Function Pack Enquire Now Accommodation Located in the south of Brisbane, Sunnybank Hotel is the ideal location to conveniently access all that Sunnybank has to offer. Stay in one of our tidy & affordable rooms, each with free WiFi, tea and coffee making facilities and microwaves, heating and cooling, and televisions. Enjoy the recently renovated hotel next door, with offers only available to in-house guests. We're located in the heart of Sunnybank, on the doorstep of the Nissan Sporting arena, QSAC Stadium and within walking distance to the Sunnybank Plaza shopping & cinema precinct and the Sunnybank Private hospital.
