name: Manly Hotel
homepage_content: The Manly Hotel, Manly, QLD Please enable JavaScript to use this page! For full functionality of this site it is necessary to enable JavaScript. Here are the instructions how to enable JavaScript in your web browser . The Manly Hotel In the heart of the Manly Harbour Village Eat Drink Functions Stay Gaming Serving locals by the sea since 1960 Welcome to the Manly Hotel. A welcome door to locals and beyond, where we live for the 'what have you been up to's' and the 'fancy seeing you here's'. Whether you‚Äôre dropping in for a quick beer with a mate, or you‚Äôre in the area, it‚Äôs the perfect place relax, unwind and take a breath. A local favourite since the 60's, we‚Äôve seen it all. Milestones, special occasions, casual catch ups and more, we‚Äôre less about goodbyes and more into 'see ya later‚Äô. A place to just enjoy yourself, the big things don‚Äôt seem so serious inside our four walls. If you‚Äôre a local of the area, or just heading down for a day trip, we‚Äôll have something to suit what you‚Äôre after. Find your way into our Courtyard, and pull up a chair or better yet, grab a table for the whole crew, where there's always room for one more. It's the perfect place to share a drink and soak up Manly's buzzing atmosphere. Or for those after a bite, our Restaurant is where our food comes to life, there's and always a chip to steal from someone's plate. We might‚Äôve added a lick of paint or two as the years have gone by, but the way we go about it will always be the same. We‚Äôre no fuss, no stress, where everyone is welcome for a drink. Come say g'day. View Menu Book Now WHAT'S ON The Courtyard Sitting across from our Inner Terrace, The Courtyard is a breath of fresh air against the hustle and bustle of everyday life. The perfect spot to catch up on life's happenings with loved ones, grab a cocktail and relax, enjoying the buzzing atmosphere of Manly and an abundance of natural light. Grab a table big enough for the whole crew, where there's always room for one more. You'll have your choice of 16 beer taps, as well as a wide variety of cocktails, wine and spirits, to suit any occasion. The Courtyard is a local favourite, a central meeting spot for friends new and old to put a pause on the nine-to-five. Restaurant Our restaurant is the perfect spot for an overdue family catch up, a quick lunch with your mates, or an intimate date night. We believe in not having to sacrifice on good quality food, by keeping it local. Inspired by our close proximity to the harbour, our menu is seasonal, featuring fresh seafood sourced locally and sustainably. Plus, all the classics you know and love, including succulent steaks, fresh salads and hearty chicken parmi's (perfect for stealing a bite of). With a touch of Mediterranean charm, our restaurant is one of our most-loved spaces to enjoy the very best of Manly dining. With something for the little ones, seniors and everyone in between. Book a table now. View Menu Book Now The Inner Terrace If there's one thing we understand, it's the need to unwind, our Inner Terrace is the spot in the Harbour to do just that. Where you hear 'Cheers!' ring out regularly, and the occasional 'What game are you watching ump'. With live sport across three large screens, you won't miss a minute of the game. Plus 16 ice-cold beers on tap to choose from, it's the ideal place to spend an afternoon (or an early knockoff from work). View Menu Functions We believe in celebrating life's moments the right way, with a mix of energy, excitement and made to be enjoyed exactly how you'd like. Let us celebrate with you. With various function spaces, tailored to match the style you're after. Our team on the ground are there to make sure everyhting runs smoothly, so you can sit back and enjoy. Enquire today. homepage_content: Transit Tavern, Brisbane Airport, QLD Please enable JavaScript to use this page! For full functionality of this site it is necessary to enable JavaScript. Here are the instructions how to enable JavaScript in your web browser . Welcome To The Transit Tavern A Favourite of Brisbane's Airport Eat Functions Stuck In Transit? If you're stuck in transit, why not spend it in comfort? The Transit Tavern has been a comfortable and accommodating space for those passing through or coming home for years. Take a seat and enjoy a delicious meal with fresh ingredients sourced from local suppliers. We're the ideal place to relax and soak in the bustling atmosphere around you. With a selection of beer, wine, cider and spirits, and delicious freshly brewed coffee, the Transit Tavern is the best place to be. View Menu Book Now WHAT'S ON Dining Transit Tavern is open for breakfast, lunch and dinner seven days a week. We‚Äôre the perfect spot to sit and relax while stuck in transit, or while waiting for friends and family. We offer delicious food, drinks and coffee, with great service, making your experience at Brisbane's airport the best it can be. Book a table online or head in and speak with our friendly team. View Menu Book Now Breakfast Menu Functions Stuck in transit and need somewhere with a comfortable and welcoming atmosphere to unwind while you wait? Or just looking for friendly and professional service? The Transit Tavern is perfect for you! With daily chef specials, everyday drink and food specials that change monthly; breakfast, lunch, tapas, platters and cocktail menus available on request and an extensive coffee and cake range to choose from, why would you go anywhere else? Whether you're just looking for fantastic coffee to have in or to takeaway, or hosting a function for friends or colleagues, the staff at the Transit Tavern are here to make your Transit experience a pleasant one. name: Strand Park
homepage_content: The Strand - Townsville City Council Skip to content Skip to navigation You are here: Home Facilities & Recreation Parks, Beaches & Community Venues The Strand The Strand Discover The Strand The Strand is a 2.2km world-class beachfront promenade custom-built for enjoyment. Along this palm tree lined stretch are bike and walkway paths, safe swimming beaches, picturesque picnic spots, playgrounds, exercise stations, a water park and restaurants and bars with to-die-for water views. You can enjoy the free family fun of The Strand Water Park, fish off the pier, choose to get active with a jog, or simply laze on the beach and enjoy the million-dollar views of Magnetic Island. The Strand offers the best of all worlds. Expand all The Strand Rockpool The Strand Rockpool is a stinger resistant seawater pool located on the northern end of The Strand. With easy access to a wide range of facilities, The Strand Rockpool is the perfect place to enjoy a picnic or barbeque and cool off for free! The pool is gently sloped with a shallow area suitable for wheelchair access and children, which leads into a deeper pool for swimming. Facilities toilets (male, female and disabled access) barbeque and picnic facilities children‚Äôs playground outdoor showers Parking available on Howitt Street and The Strand promenade (including four disabled parking bays). View the virtual tour (YouTube). Opening Hours Please note: services may be subject to change. Lifeguard on duty daily ‚Äì see schedule for availability. Closed every Wednesday for cleaning, excluding public holidays. Strand Park Strand Park is a family-friendly space offering something for everyone. With a sprawling grass playing field, half basketball court, playground and accessible beach, Strand Park is ideal for the active beachgoer. Facilities grass playing field toilets (male, female and disabled access) barbecue and picnic facilities half basketball court teenage playground (near the playing field) junior playground on the pier side of the beach outdoor showers beach access mats onto The Strand Beach are available from each week from 10:30am Friday to 3pm Saturday, as well as for special events on The Strand Beach. Parking available on The Strand promenade surrounding the playing field (including six disabled parking bays). For more information visit: the Strand Park page on Popular Parks & Playgrounds. The Strand Water Park The Strand Water Park is ever popular with families with kids. Kids will have a blast cooling off in the water park, with slides, water cannons and much more to enjoy. Facilities children‚Äôs water park junior children‚Äôs playground toilets (male, female and disabled access) barbeque and picnic facilities outdoor showers. Parking available along The Strand promenade (including four disabled parking bays). Opening Hours Please note: services may be subject to change. Lifeguard on duty daily ‚Äì see schedule for availability. Closed every Tuesday for maintenance, excluding Queensland State School holidays and public holidays. Beach Access Mats Wheelchairs, prams and strollers can access The Strand on mats every day except from 4pm Thursday afternoon to 9am Friday morning. The Strand Water Park. Half basketball court in Strand Park. The Strand Pier. BBQ and picnic facilities. The Strand Water Park. Strand Beach. Outdoor fitness equipment along The Strand. The Strand Rockpool. Swings at The Strand Rockpool. Strand Park. Welcome to the Upper Ross Hotel A Local Favourite in Rasmussen Eat Drink Stay Gaming Your Friendly Pub by the Ross River In the Townsville suburb of Rasmussen, Upper Ross Hotel offers a range of facilities for everyone to enjoy. Nestled on Riverway Drive, just near the banks of the Ross River, we‚Äôre the ideal place to settle in with family and friends. If you‚Äôve been coming for a while, we probably know your drink. If you‚Äôre stopping in for the first time, you'll feel right at home when you walk through the doors. Our Bistro serves up pub classics including juicy steaks, crispy schnitzels and fish n chips, plus kids‚Äô meals and regular specials to keep the whole family happy. Watch the game in a relaxed and friendly environment perfect for catching up with friends or well deserved knock-off drink at the end of a hard day. If you‚Äôre looking for affordable accommodation, our Hotel is perfect for long or short term stays. Guests can relax and escape the North Queensland heat in affordable air conditioned rooms. At the Upper Ross, we're here for you on the good days, the bad days and every day in between, so head in to enjoy your local in Rasmussen. View Menu Book Now WHAT'S ON bistro Head to the Upper Ross Bistro and tuck into a quality pub meal the whole family will enjoy. With a focus on sourcing locally and sustainably, we offer a menu with a range of pub food, from salads to steaks, schnitzels, burgers and all of your pub classics. With a kids' menu, seniors dishes and regular specials, we've got something for everyone. Make a booking today View Menu Book Now Bistro bar We're a local, for the locals. The Upper Ross Bistro Bar is the perfect place to catch up with mates, stop by for an after work drink or settle in for the big game. Whatever the occasion, our friendly staff are serving up ice cold beer and cider, plus a range of wine and spirits. Grab a bite to eat and enjoy a good feed while sipping on your favourite drink. We have regular promos and events running throughout the week so make sure you drop in to the Upper Ross Hotel today. Accommodation Our accommodation provides affordable convenience (in air conditioning!) for guests visiting from out of town. Just 25 minutes from Townsville and the Great Barrier Reef, Upper Ross Hotel is perfect for visitors wanting to experience all that the north east of Queensland has to offer. Guests can relax and escape the North Queensland heat in affordable air conditioned rooms. Each room features a TV, bar sized refrigerator and tea/coffee making facilities, as well as access to shared bathroom and guest laundry. If you‚Äôre looking for a base to explore the north east of Queensland, the Upper Ross Hotel is the place for you. Whether staying for a few nights or just one, we strive to make each guest feel comfortable and at ease; like visiting an old friend. homepage_content: Saleyards draft Precinct Plan - phase 2 consultation | Have Your Say Skip to main content Close Saleyards Draft Precinct Plan - Phase 2 consultation We‚Äôve prepared a Precinct Plan for the Saleyards. It sets out the vision, future uses and development principles that will guide this exciting new residential precinct. Follow Listen This engagement is closed. Contributions to this engagement have closed. A report has been prepared on the consultation findings which can be found in the Document Library. Project Update This plan was adopted by Council on 22 June 2021. The plan sets out the background, design principles, land use and layout for the saleyards precinct (former saleyards and Target headquarters sites in North Geelong) as it transitions to a proposed mixed-use high density residential precinct. The City will now prepare a planning scheme amendment to introduce new zone and overlay controls to deliver the precinct plan. The amendment will include a public exhibition period (late 2021) and opportunities for submissions. You can see the adopted plan here OVERVIEW The City has prepared a draft Precinct Plan outlining a framework plan, design concepts and design principles for the Saleyards site. These reflect and build on the ideas shared in last year‚Äôs community vision workshop. At its meeting on Tuesday 26 May 2020, the City of Greater Geelong Council resolved to support the release of the draft Saleyards Precinct Plan for public consultation. We would love to hear what you think of the draft Precinct Plan as part of the phase 2 community consultation. This feedback will be used to further refine the Precinct Plan before it is finalised and presented to Council for adoption in mid-late 2020. View Saleyards Draft Precinct Plan Note: Technical reports have informed the preparation of the draft Precinct Plan and the findings are summarised in the draft Plan on pages 10-14. If you would like to discuss any aspects of the technical reports please contact us. FEEDBACK CLOSED Select one or all of the tools below to have your say: Written submission - use the online form to provide feedback. Social Map - using the concept plan as a base map to drop your comments and ideas onto features of the Plan. Survey - let us know using the survey whether you support the design principles and outcomes of the draft Plan. Register for an on-line meeting here or one-on-one phone interviews here (details below). Alternatively, contact us on 5272 5078 and we can post you hardcopies of the documents and/or feedback forms and you can write to The Coordinator, Planning Strategy, PO Box 104, Geelong, Vic 3220. name: Sage Yellowfin
homepage_content: Yellowfin Seafood & Grill | Southbank Restaurant & Bar | 07 31299398 Sage Yellowfin Where culinary excellence meets global flavours Book Your Table Now About Sage Yellowfin At Sage Yellowfin, we want you to explore diverse cuisine from around the world. Whether you are a fan of exotic spices or international delicacies, our curated menu caters for every palate. We source the finest ingredients collaborating with Brisbane leading fresh produce suppliers and local markets in Queensland. We look forward to Welcoming you at our Modern Australian restaurant to create memorable dining experience. 07 31299398 Book a table THE BAR We invite you to step into our haven of liquid artistry, where we take pride in curating an exquisite selection of wines Using premium spirits, fresh ingredients and a dash of imaginations, our skilled mixologists create cocktails that are visually stunning as they are delightful to drink. Join us for an unforgettable experience in a world of wines and handcrafted cocktails. Clients feedback What our customer says about our food & service Delicious food, friendly staff and a stunning location. This was our first family dinner outing since moving to Brisbane and we absolutely love it here! Thank you team Ailean Naidu (Brisbane) Had a fantastic experience at Yellowfin for our 20th Anniversary, the beautiful staff and amazing food made our meal unforgettable, Thankyou Yellowfin Southbank Brooke Hawkings (Brisbane) I always love coming back here. It's our go to in Brissy for an amazing meal. The menu is excellent and the fish is always the star of every dish (we always have seafood here). Drinks are good and the staff always great. Cameron Tanner (Brisbane) The cold and hot seafood platter were both superb! Good value and tasted so good! We'll be back. Janeth Golpo (Brisbane) Great food and friendly staff made this pre-show lunch very enjoyable. A good wine list meant that the meal was paired nicely. Moray Falconer (Brisbane) Great location and service and the food has been excellent every time we have dined here. One of our favourite places to eat! Robert Holmes (Brisbane) Food was AMAZING! Beautifully made cocktails to compliment a delightful dish Vanessa Stritzke (Brisbane) Make a Reservation

name: The Pav Bar
homepage_content: The Pav Bar | Located On The Brisbane River Back to the top √ó Welcome to The Pav Bar! Nestled in the heart of Brisbane‚Äôs CBD, The Pav Bar is the perfect spot to unwind, dine, and soak up the vibrant inner-city atmosphere. Whether you prefer to relax indoors or enjoy the fresh air in our open-air courtyard, we offer an inviting setting for any occasion. Indulge in a mouthwatering selection of tasty eats, juicy burgers, and refreshing beverages that pair perfectly with Brisbane‚Äôs laid-back vibe. From quick lunches to after-work drinks , we‚Äôve got your cravings covered. Sip on a twilight cocktail , kick back with a cold beer, or share a bottle of wine with friends‚Äîour extensive drinks menu caters to all tastes. Love live sports? So do we! Catch all the action on our big-screen TVs , making the ultimate spot to cheer on your favourite team while enjoying great food and drinks. Planning a casual get-together? Whether it‚Äôs sundowners with colleagues, a catch-up with friends, or a weekend wind-down , we set the perfect scene for socialising in Brisbane‚Äôs bustling CBD. Discover why we‚Äôre more than just a bar‚Äîit‚Äôs a Brisbane hotspot for good times, great food, and unbeatable atmosphere . Visit us today and experience it for yourself! There‚Äôs more to the Pav Bar than meets the eye. Book your next party at The Pav Bar! No matter what the occasion, gather your friends and colleagues and head to the Pav Bar for a great value group gathering. Our super cool venue sets the scene for the perfect celebration.
